@NODE "Mail_0" "(Off topic a bit)  Sorry."
 for scott@online.u-net.com; Sat, 3 Apr 1999 00:41:29 +0000
From: Andrew Bruno <abruno@zeta.org.au>
Date: Sat, 03 Apr 1999 10:18:16 +1000
Subject: (Off topic a bit)  Sorry.

Hi,

Well it was here I heard of it, so it is here I shall ask:

I have got TV Paint, and it is AMZAING!

Ok, I also have IFX, and it is good, and I have not learnt how to use it
properly.  But the effects in TV-Paint are great.

(Enough plugging)

Since TVP has been "released" I don't remember seeing the doc's for it at
the site.

(I am trying hard to get my PPC card working so I am mostly concentrating on
that at the moment too)

Anyone know from where you can get the docs?

Please....

Cya!
-- 
PUNNY BOOK = In The Trenches: Helmut Wearer.


Andrew Bruno
abruno@zeta.org.au



