 for scott@online.u-net.com; Sun, 4 Apr 1999 16:24:47 +0000
From: Mikkel =?iso-8859-1?Q?L=F8kke?= <flameduck@software.dk>
Date: Sun, 04 Apr 1999 16:36:36 +0200
Organization: M2 productions
Subject: Re: (off topic) Amiga and ASDL
Encoding: quoted-printable

Hello Stephen.

On 04-Apr-99, Stephen Lebed wrote:

> Sorry for this off topic message, but you guys might have an answer for=
 me.

Indeed.

> In the area I live in, the phone company has an ASDL service for very l=
ittle
> money.  I'd like to set up a server using one of my Amigas so I can hos=
t
> some online gaming.  Do you know if there is router that will allow me =
> use an asdl line?

Yes, there are plenty ! Allthough I think you might have to get Miami DeL=
uxe to use it. Anyway, most ADSL Routers, or "Modems" (As they are called=
 by most PC owners, that don't know what a modem is.) come equiped with o=
ne or more 10-base-T Twisted Pair Ethernet plugs. So get an Ariadne II an=
d you should be cruising.

Allthough yoou might want to find out what upstream/]downstream bandwidth=
 you get for "very little money". Over here we "only" get 256Kb downstrea=
m, and 128Kb upstream.


Regards
-- =


