@NODE "Mail_9" "** YEAH! BFB Done!. Check this out ;) **"
 for scott@online.u-net.com; Thu, 22 Apr 1999 09:13:28 +0000
From: Rob Hutchinson <loki@napalmdeath.freeserve.co.uk>
Date: Thu, 22 Apr 1999 09:05:54 +0100
Organization: Satanic Dreams Software.
Subject: ** YEAH! BFB Done!. Check this out ;) **

--BOUNDARY.274339752.1

Hello,

  Ok, me and David McMinn now finished the conversion of the bfbplayer
C code (Oh thats 2 now ;) oooooooOoooOOo)....

Befor I go on, sorry if this is a bit big but I haven`t posted anything
even remotly large for ages so I`m making up for it ;) eheheheh.

Anyways, I`ve just finished my SDSBFBPlayer V1.00 (attached), and i`m
wondering if you nice chappies can test it out before I upload it to
aminet. It SHOULD in theory support 12 types of module, most of which
I dont have :(((((.

 1, ProTracker        <-- Tested seems fine ;) 
 2, MED / OctaMED    <-- Tested seems fine
 3, QuadraComposer  <-- What the hell is that? ;)
 4, The Player 6.0a   <-- Not got one of these, anyone ?
 5, The Player 6.1a   <-- Had one once, not anymore :(
 6, David Whittaker   <-- Eeeeeek!!! Anyone?
 7, GMOD              <-- Bit obscure me thinks ??
 8, DigiBooster      <-- I think it only supports version 1, definatly dont
                            work with any I`ve got :(((. Can anyone confirm?
 9, PSID             <-- I can test this later if noone else does ;)
 10, THX Sound System <-- What the hell is that?
 11, Oktalyzer            <-- Earlier OctaMed? Anyone got one?
 12, BMOD                 <-- Dont think ANYONE has one of them?

To sum up, I testing MED and MOD, cos I aint got any others.. ahahahaha! ;)

Also, can someone test it for inforcer hits for me please, I dont have an
MMU so I cant do this :(((. The author of BFB says that Player60A causes
enforcer hits. But I`m more worried about my routines BFBNextPattern{}
and BFBPrevPattern{} causing enforcer hits (try pattern jumping in the
exe pweez). The reason I think it`ll cause enforcer hits is cos I was
getting overflow errors from the 2 above commands when overflow checking
was switched on,.. and it`s fine without. It`s down to the types I think,
but I couldn`t be arsed to fix it ;)..

What you will require to run the EXE,
 the libs from Libs/#? copying to your libs: dir
 PlaySID.library for sid playback
 MedPlayer.library for MED playback

If ya gonna use the include, and or my program, you require,
 SDSBFB.RES in BlitzLibs:
 bfbplaymaster.library1 in BlitzLibs:AmigaLibs/
 <re-compile deflibs ;)>
 And in the source you need amigalibs.res + SDSBFB.RES resident in the 
 compiler menu. 
 You need BSS as well ;)

Using the SDSBFBPlayer:
 o Files are loaded 100% by drag and drop ;).. Then scanned, and played.
    So just drag a module from a WB or dopus lister.
 o From Left to Right:
    Play,Cont,Stop,PrevPattern,NextPattern,Eject,Fold-Unfold.
    ModInfo should give you some extra information on the currently
    loaded module, including sample names ;)
 o Should run fine from both WB and CLI, in the CLI type:
    SDSBFBPlayer ?      -> for help
 o All GUI elements except the Fold-UnFold button and the Project menu
    are locked out until you load a module.
 o Dont forget the right mouse button menus ;)
 o To load a new module just drop a new one into the window ;). or you
    could eject the current one first, it makes no difference ;)

All in a day or two`s work,.. not bad really, SDSBFBPlayer and the include
took me only 11 hours... Eeeeeeek! Between major help from David ;)

BTW - this is just a test, before I write the docs for the include, and
        the player.. I want to make sure it is working correctly ;)

See Gaz, there you go, we wrote ya multi-module format player for ya ;)
ahahaha, all ya have to do now is use the includes in the archive, and
away ya go ;)

Ta, hope this helps someone ;)

DONT FORGET THOSE LIBS BEFORE RUNNING THE EXE ! ;)

Cya!
-- 
