Yeah I`m sorry about that, I was in a MAJOR rush,.. I just slapped the
GUI together as fast as possible (as you can tell, has nothing on
h0L0-Player ;)))))... I wanted it just as an example to go with my includes
, nuffin else, but I am going to write a nice little tidy version and probs
release it if it`s good enough ;).. Cos I need a new mod player (Hippo
spaks, Eagleplayer 1 and 2 are poo, and delitracker,... WELL ;)..) Even
though it only supports 12 types of module, it is still a cool little lib to
have, and from what I can tell, it`s not very processor intesive with mod
or med at least ;).. 

BTW - You can use the BFB libs with freeware/sharware and commercial
        software without any probs,. although you do require written
        permission from the author to release BFB with a commercial 
        package.. He seems to have done a runner ;)

[=> Maybe do the same with the .Screen\WBorLeft and \WborRight in case
[=> these have been adjusted to non standard sizes ?

Yeah sorry about this, it is my fault for rushing it and not testing it
with other fonts. Like I said it is a right bodge, just as an example to go
with our work..

Time to do the docs me thinks ;)...

Cya!

