>> the sample names etc., which worked OK until I pressed the windows
>> close gadget and then it was "Hello Mr Guru, come on in, make yourself
>> comfortable" time :(
> 
> Did you have Visual Prefs running?
> 
> I'm getting all sorts of bug reports when closing windows/etc that
> the program crashes. Turns out the people reporting these problems
> all have Visual Prefs running. :(
> 
> There was talk about stopping this "Unable To Free Memory" conflict
> out a while ago - can someone please tell me how to stop that damn
> program messing our Blitz programs up??

I don't have Visual Prefs, and it works fine here...  So, you are probably
right.

But here is the cure, or so I am told:

The problem is that VP attaches an image to the GTgadgets (making them into
"shape" gadgets, as it were) so when Blitz tries to free the gadgetlist
memory, it can't (because it doesn't know about the images).

So, the cure is this,

Before freeing a GTlist, or ending your program, you put in a dummy
errortrap:

SetErr
EndSetErr

Free GTList 0

ClrErr

Blitz still can't free the memory, of course, but now the error is bypassed,
so no GURU...  I don't know what happens to the images, maybe VP frees
them?

                                    Yours electronically,
                                    Curt Esser
                                    camge@ix.netcom.com
                                    http://members.xoom.com/Curt_Esser/



