@NODE "Mail_31" "Re: ** YEAH! BFB Done!. Check this out ;) **"
 for scott@online.u-net.com; Mon, 26 Apr 1999 03:18:02 +0100
Date: Mon, 26 Apr 1999 17:44:56 +1200
From: Julian Kinraid <jkinraid@clear.net.nz>
X-Accept-Language: en-GB,en
Subject: Re: ** YEAH! BFB Done!. Check this out ;) **
Encoding: 7bit

Curt Esser wrote:

[snip VP stuff]

> Before freeing a GTlist, or ending your program, you put in a dummy
> errortrap:
> 
> SetErr
> EndSetErr
> 
> Free GTList 0
> 
> ClrErr
> 
> Blitz still can't free the memory, of course, but now the error is bypassed,
> so no GURU...  I don't know what happens to the images, maybe VP frees
> them?

I think what happened was that Blitz would call the Blitz freemem
routine, which searches a list of the allocations done by the Blitz
allocmem routine.  When it finds out the pointer to the image isn't in
the list, it barfs.  The SetErr stuff just stops Blitz from barfing,
because in reality, no error has actually occured.  Because VP allocated
the images, it is probably up to either VP or Intuition to free them.

--
Julian Kinraid ....... jkinraid@clear.net.nz ....... ICQ:17257217


