NewType .Hello
  Test.l
  Tester.s
  Testme.w
End NewType

; Now make sure all other residents are clear in the compiler menu,
; + Switch off the debugger (cos it causes problems for me ;)))
; and select Compile and Run from the menus,. Now click the 
; Create Resident menu item and select a .RES file. (best place to
; put it is in BlitzLibs: ) ;).. Simple. Now is you open another
; document (RAMIGA+P) and put BlitzLibs:Test.RES in the compiler menu
; and open the NewTypes informantion, you should have 1 type in there
; (unless you got summat else resident), 1 type: Hello..
; Simple? Well, the blitz manually is a croc of shit, we all know that ;)

