the structures and stuff are usually in .h files (is that right? I cant
remember ;)).. But yeah they are in there somewhere ;)

[=> And does anyone know how to convert them ?

Thats what I been trying to learn how to do,... It`s as good as any place
to start learning C ;)

Well basically, (in C at least), 

struct Hello - would convert to: NEWTYPE .Hello
And the rest is simple,
APTR is a pointer variable: *   (is that right?)
 APTR Test  --->  *Test
LONG is a longword variable: .l
 LONG Test  --->  Test.l
WORD is a wordtype variable: .w
 WORD Test  --->  Test.w
etc..
etc....
You get the picture?
END NEWTYPE

Do you have C code to hand? If not look at the NewIcons4 stuff, thats
where I started ;).. But I`ve already converted that so theres no need,
I`ll send it to ya if ya want it?

