Dave churned out *this* drivel:

> Ignore that last message, LHA uses little endian format....(intel
> etc)...which means that their words and longs byte orders are
> reversed...ie
> 
> our word (big endian)
> 
> byte 2, byte 1
> 
> there word (little endian)
> 
> byte 1, byte 2
> 
> So you need to swap all the 4 bytes around to change it from little
> endian, to big endian as used on 680x0....

Thanks for pointing that out, or I'd never have got it - the docs do say
that it's little endian, but I never understood what that meant until now :)

