@NODE "Mail_44" "Re: 4-bytes -> Long value?"
 for scott@online.u-net.com; Thu, 22 Apr 1999 04:28:28 +0100
From: "Dave" <dave@nbsamiga.demon.co.uk>
Subject: Re: 4-bytes -> Long value?
Date: Thu, 22 Apr 1999 04:27:49 +0100
	charset="iso-8859-1"
Encoding: 7bit

Ignore that last message, LHA uses little endian format....(intel
etc)...which means that their words and longs byte orders are reversed...ie

our word (big endian)

byte 2, byte 1

there word (little endian)

byte 1, byte 2

So you need to swap all the 4 bytes around to change it from little endian,
to big endian as used on 680x0....

Dave


