Make sure your ASM is right. If you were just going to do MOVE.l blah,blah=
 then 
xxxReg (make sure this is the corerect command too, I always have to look =
up 
what they do), make sure that the values you are starting with are correct=
. 
Make sure you have the fixed acidlibs file, as sometimes the third paramet=
er is 
screwed up in statements and functions.

> I think that was something to do with registers not being preserved or
> something, but is there a fix for it? I thought AsmExit had something to
> do with it, but I didn't understand that...

Preserve a4 (local variables) and a5 (global variables). I think AsmExit i=
s 
used when you want an entire function of ASM, and/or you are trying to ret=
urn 
the value in d0.


