> the other Screen stuff works, but not the bitmap.
>
> The only way I can get the depth of the WB is by using the Blitz WBdepth
> command or by grabbing the Screen's bitmap, and reading the Blitz bitmap
> object. Neither method will work on a GFX card screen, I don't think.
> 
> Anybody else gotten this to work?

 Yes I normally do:
*SCR.Screen=3DPeek.l(Addr Screen(0))
dpth.b=3D*SCR\RastPort\BitMap\Depth

 RastPort and BitMap may need _ in front of them if you use amigalibsii.re=
s. 
Note the capitalization of the words. And the reason I go through the rast=
port 
is because you are told to use the rastport for drawing onto the screens 
bitmap, as a bitmap can't be expanded properly to cover screen depths>8 
(according to the os3.1 includes anyway), so I use it for getting the bitm=
ap 
data as well.


