Here's a function that gets the WB screen's depth, but it turns out that
WBDepth (the Blitz command) creates a smaller executable...

Can anyone tell me what this returns on a gfx card - I made it return
a long value in case it does work on >8 bit screens (you can make it
return the number of colours instead if you want)...

See ya,
-- 
<tsb>
<sb>James L Boyd - jamesboyd@all-hail.freeserve.co.uk
<sb>Member of Team *AMIGA*, and *Dogbert's New Ruling Class.*
<sb>Connected from Dundee, Scotland. 
<sb>(http://surf.to/all-hail/)
<tsb>

You have not converted a man because you have silenced him.
-- John Morley

--BOUNDARY.1747478776.1
Content-Disposition: attachment; filename="NewWBDepth.asc"
Content-Description: Returns WB depth or no of colours

Function.l NewWBDepth {coloursflag.b}

  *sc.Screen=LockPubScreen_ ("Workbench")

  If *sc
    deep.w=*sc\_RastPort\_BitMap\Depth

;    deep.w=*sc\RastPort\BitMap\Depth

; NOTE - if you get "offset not found", try uncommenting the
; above line and commenting out the original...different versions
; of amigalibs.res have different offset names...

    UnlockPubScreen_ "Workbench",*sc
  EndIf

  If coloursflag
    Function Return 2^deep
  Else Function Return deep
  EndIf

End Function

; demo :

NPrint NewWBDepth {0} ; change 0 to -1 (actually, any word-range value)
                      ; to get it to return colours instead of depth
MouseWait:End



--BOUNDARY.1747478776.1

