    Hi Tony, =


> I'm going to try to make my GT  GUI font sensitive and also convert
> the program to NCS.   Which should I do first.   My gut feeling is NCS
> first.   Any thoughts?

    Yes, convert it to NCS first.
 =

> Given that I've got one screen (#0), three windows (#0,1,2) and 47
> GTLists (#guess what??)  when I go NCS, should I try and change all at
> once or do the screen first, then the windows, then the gadgets or the
> gadgets first, then  windows, then screen.   Also,  there is an
> NInitGadget command (plus similar for the windows etc.)   Is the
> argument to this the highest gadget number, the total number of
> gadgets or the number in use simultaneously?
> I.e if I have gadgets numbered 1,3,5,7  with only one in use at any
> time, do I NinitGadget 1, NInitGadget 4 or NInitGadget 7??

    The NInitXXXX commands are the same than the max object number
in the 'Compiler' window of the BB2. The number you must pass to an
NInitXXX command is the number max of object you are authorized to
use. And if you want one more, you must increase this number. A great
advantage is than each NInitXXX routine return 0 if it fails or
a value <> 0 (not -1 !) else. So if one of the NInitXXX command
fails, stop immediately your program and write a little message
which say there is an error at the initialization.

    Bye,
