@NODE "Mail_71" "SV: A few quick questions"
 for scott@online.u-net.com; Sat, 17 Apr 1999 12:03:26 +0000
From: "Andreas Hĺkansson" <andy.h@telia.com>
Subject: SV: A few quick questions
Date: Sat, 17 Apr 1999 13:02:30 +0200


>I somehow hate peeks and pokes and addr commands. But what I meant was
>attaching an NCS gadget with the attachgtlist command, that doesnt work.
And I
>think thats what the original mailer meant. I mean attachgtlist is for
>easier and more obvious than peeking around. And what is that * b4 the
>mylist?


It seems to me that you want use more "advanced" features without having to
do the
dirty work. Peek and Poke are very usefull, and without them you may as well
stick to
the normal blitz libs..

Not putting you down, but it's like the old saying "you cant both have the
cake and eat it
at the same time".

and the * means it's a pointer... when you do

*MyList = NCreateGadgetList(0, Peek.l(Addr Screen(0))

It returns a pointer to the gadget list, which you then need when you want
do anything with it..like

AddGList_ Peek.l(Addr Window(0), *MyList, 0, 0)

for example--



