encoding: Quoted-printable
Subject: Re: A few quick questions

> >     You're totally wrong here too, as you can use the magic line below
> >     to
> > attach an NCS gadgetlist to your 'Blitz' window (but I can't see the
> > purpose) :
> > AddGList_ Peek.l(Addr Window(0), *MyList, 0, 0)

 Actually, that would need to be AddGList_ Peek.l(Addr Window(0)),*MyList,=
-1,0

 The -1 says to add all gadgets, and you had the ) in the wrong place.

> I want to convert a huge program to NCS.    If I do it all in one go
> then it will be a pain debugging any problems.   If I change a few
> bits at a time then if it breaks, I know where to look.
> 
> Is the best way to ghange gadget lists, one or two at a time; then do th=
e
> menus, then the windows, then the Screen.     Or the other way round?

 I'd say yes. Gadget lists and menus are easy to add to regular Blitz wind=
ows, 
even the ones from the NCS. Screens and windows - depends how you open the=
m. It 
won't matter if you use WindowTags as both that command and the NCS ones w=
ould 
use the tag for specifying a screen, rather than having an already used sc=
reen.


