@NODE "Mail_81" "A possible way to get fast animation & good packing ratio easely"
 for scott@online.u-net.com; Sat, 17 Apr 1999 12:35:42 +0000
From: Frederic Laboureur <alphasnd@sdv.fr>
Date: Sat, 17 Apr 1999 07:43:35 +0100
Organization: Fantaisie Software
Subject: A possible way to get fast animation & good packing ratio easely
Encoding: quoted-printable


    Hi Blitzers,

    I've followed your discution about the 'possible' new animation forma=
t
(in chunky mode) and may be the XPK library can help you because it has
a real fast/good Packer: NUKE. It depack about 600 kb/sec on a 68030/25
so it should overtake the 1 Mb/s on a 040/25.

    As it packs very well, you should save the each chunky frame in a
raw form and pack each independently with NUKE. After, you put all
the frames in one single file with extra infos for each frame and
you use load/depack one frame each after other directly into
the video memory buffer...

    Possible format:

Size of the Frame (packed)
Extra info about the palette...
Frame data

    I my humble opinion, we should achieve at least 12,5 fps in 320*200
256 colour mode.
    =

    I hope this will help,
 =

                        Fred.

