Hi all, =


Just received this from Neil Bothwick at the new Amiga Active magazine (w=
hich
is going to kick AF off the face of the earth if they keep up their recen=
t
standards)...

Anyone who has good quality stuff, send it to 'em :)

*** Begin of forwarded message ***

Date: 22-Apr-99 08:38:40
From: Neil Bothwick <aacd@amigactive.com>
Subject: Re: AACD Submissions

--- Forwarded message follows ---


>Hi,
>Can you send me the submission details for the AACD?
>Cheers :)
>James L Boyd - jamesboyd@all-hail.freeserve.co.uk


We welcome readers' submissions for the Amigactive CD. We would like to
receive programs, games, graphics, animations and musical creations. Do n=
ot
send anything unless you have permission to do so. This includes your own=

creations if they contain copyrighted material, such as samples of other
music in mods.

You may submit your work on disk or via the Internet. Postal
submissions should be sent to

    AACD Submissions
 =A0=A0=A0Amigactive Magazine,
    Systems House
    3/11 Spring Road
    Bournemouth
    Dorset
    BH1 4PZ

in one of the following disk formats

    Amiga floppy disk: 880KB or 1.76MB
    PC floppy disk: 720KB or 1.44MB
    Zip disk: Amiga or PC format
    CD: ISO, Rockridge or Joliet format

If sending floppy disks, please use standard disk formats and do not send=

archives created with a backup program. If you send LhA or LZX archives,
make sure you check the archive for corruption before sending. If we cann=
ot
read your disks, your submission will not appear on the CD. All submissio=
ns
must be accompanied by the permission statement below.


Internet submissions

You may upload your work to the cdsubmissions directory of our FTP site,

    Address:    ftp.wirenet.co.uk
    Login:      aacd
    Password:   readers

Each upload must be accompanied by a separate readme file containing your=

name, email address, a brief description of your submission and the
permission statement below. For example, if you upload MyProgram.lha and
MyMods.lha you must also upload MyProgram.readme and MyMods.readme. Any
archive uploaded without a readme will not be considered for the CD.
Files may be archived with LZX, LhA, ZIP or tar/gzip (tgz). Please be sur=
e
to check archives for corruption before uploading, if we can't read it we=

can't include it.

Web site submissions

Please mail first if you wish your web site to be included on an AACD.
The address is aacd.websites@amigactive.com

The above requirements regarding readme files apply to web site uploads t=
oo.



Permission to include material on an Amigactive CD
=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=
=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=



I, ...... give permission for, ...... to be included on any Amigactive
CD. I have the right to grant this permission, no other copyrights
would be infringed by such inclusion.

Name:
