On 24 Apr 99 Rob Hutchinson wrote about 'AACD Submissions (fwd)'.

 RH> Ok Ok,. I read thru the entire original post, and all this talk of
 RH> sending website submissions, programs utils for the CD etc etc etc..

The idea behind sending websites in, rather than leeching them, is to
stop any arguments about people not being asked if the site could be
included on the cover CD. CU Amiga had some embarasing moments with
websites that were leeched, so Amigactive had adopted a 'no leech'
policy. This takes away any confusion about the placing of the site on
the CD

 RH> Sounds very AF... But like I said I`m not a fan of AF, so hopefully
 RH> AA will be much better ;)

It'll be miles better, you watch :)

 RH> Good,.. Still a little expensive but cheaper than AF,.. I can see AF

Expensive, christ, what do you people want?

 RH> going down cos of this ;) hahahah

Highly unlikely, but it will introduce some healthy competition back into
the Amiga print mag market again.

 RH> It`s depressing when you go into WHSmith and buy AF with 1 CD, and kno=
w
 RH> you could have just brought 3 PC mags with 6 CD`s :(((

But even then, you're only buying an oversized catalogue. And the CD's are
only full of useless demos mostly. Amigactive will offer plenty of editoria=
l,
technical features and articles, as well as a revolutionary cover CD. Bear=
 in
mind, it's easy to fill a CD, but to make it useful, and easy to use is
something else.

Simon Archer


