@NODE "Mail_99" "Re: Adress and length"
 for scott@online.u-net.com; Sat, 24 Apr 1999 18:05:18 +0100
From: James L Boyd <jamesboyd@all-hail.freeserve.co.uk>
Date: Sat, 24 Apr 1999 17:59:33 +0000
Subject: Re: Adress and length

amorel churned out *this* drivel:

>   void SetModule( APTR header, APTR fileLocation, UWORD fileLength );
>                          A0              A1                D0:16

>> Most important command, again the header beats me, file location is the
>> memory location of the loaded file, how to find that???? Filelength is
>> the length of the loaded file, how to find that????

Doesn't this function just fill them in for you?

I'm having to guess, but maybe this'd do it (NOTE - YAM's bolding
the *'s here - save it out!) :

DEFTYPE.l *head, *fileloc (not sure if .l is right though! Maybe .b?)
DEFTYPE.w flength (maybe *flength?)

Then you'd do :

  SetModule_ *head,*fileloc,&flength

Or maybe :

  SetModule_ &*head,&*fileloc,&flength

Then *head, *fileloc and flength would contain the values
you need (or maybe it'd be Peek.l (*fileloc) etc...)

Try some combinations of &/* if it doesn't work (make sure you
save before running, cos it'll probably GURU if you get it wrong,
but I'm sure you know that ;)

This is how I usually figure this kind of stuff out ;)

Like I say, I'm guessing, cos I haven't used it...
 
See ya,
