@NODE "Mail_100" "Advanced blitter manipulation"
 for scott@online.u-net.com; Sat, 1 May 1999 08:07:53 +0100
From: "Rick Berry" <berry@clear.net.nz>
Subject: Advanced blitter manipulation
Date: Sat, 1 May 1999 19:01:31 +1200
Encoding: 7bit

Hello. This is my first submission to this page so bear with me. I'm
trying to make a series of routines that work similar to Polyf but

1. Do it as fast as possible.
2. Can deal with more than 5 pointed filled vectors.
3. Are more flexible.

After much fiddling around I've discovered how to meddle with the
Blitter, but program I have (which is based on a C program) doesn't
work (At least it doesn't crash). I'm sure it's something simple
but I can't see it. SOMEONE HELP ME!

I also have a version in assembler, but I want to see what's wrong
with this program before I go develing back into 680x0. It doesn't
work either.

Oh, when I wrote this I was downloading the Mildred library. Maybe
it has what I want, I don't know.

Here's the program:

; Raw Blitterline Program
; By Wiremu Te Kani April 1999
; ----------------------------
; Blitter Registers
; -----------------
NEWTYPE.bitmap
  _ebwidth.w  ;even byte width of a bitmap
  _height.w   ;pixel height of bitmap
  _depth.w    ;depth, in bitplanes, of bitmap
  _pad.b[2]
  _data.l[8]  ;Max of 8 pointers to bitplanes
  _pad2.b[22]
  _isreal.w   ;=0: no bitmap present
              ;<0: bitmap present
              ;>0: bitmap present, but not ours
End NEWTYPE
#BLTCON0=$DFF040
#BLTCON1=$DFF042
#BLTAFWM=$DFF044
#BLTALWM=$DFF046
#BLTCPT=$DFF048
#BLTBPT=$DFF04C
#BLTAPT=$DFF050
#BLTDPT=$DFF054
#BLTSIZE=$DFF058
#BLTCMOD=$DFF060
#BLTBMOD=$DFF062
#BLTAMOD=$DFF064
#BLTDMOD=$DFF066
#BLTCDAT=$DFF070
#BLTBDAT=$DFF072
#BLTADAT=$DFF074

#custom=$DFF000
#DMACONR=#custom+$02  ;DMA control register (read only)
#DMAB_BLTDONE=14
BitMap 0,320,200,1
InitCopList 0,44,200,$1,8,2,0

BLITZ
CreateDisplay 0
DisplayBitMap 0,0
VWait
bmap.l=Addr BitMap(0)
x1=10:x2=100:y1=20:y2=60
Use BitMap 0
VWait
Gosub Blitline
BitMapOutput 0
MouseWait
End:End:End

.Blitline
  ; /* Reserve Blitter and wait it to be free */
  BTST.b #DMAB_BLTDONE-8,DMACONR
waitblit2: BTST.b #DMAB_BLTDONE-8,DMACONR:BNE waitblit2

  dx.w=Abs(x1-x2):dy.w=Abs(y1-y2)
  dmax.w=Max(dx,dy):dmin.w=Min(dx,dy)

  ; /* Set the minterm and shift value, activate sources A and C */
  Poke.w #BLTCON0,$BCA+((x1 AND $f)*$1000)

  ; /* Calculate Octant */
  tmp.w=0
  If dx>=dy AND x1>=x2 Then tmp+$04
  If dx<dy  AND y1>=y2 Then tmp+$04
  If dx>=dy AND y1>=y2 Then tmp+$08
  If dx<dy  AND x1>=x2 Then tmp+$08
  If dx>=dy Then tmp+$10
  ; /* Set line mode and shift value */
    tmp+1+((x1 AND $F)*$1000)
  ; /* Set sign bit */
      If $4*dmin < $2*dmax Then tmp+$40
    Poke.w #BLTCON1,tmp

  ; /* Set masks */
    Poke.w #BLTAFWM,$FFFF
    Poke.w #BLTALWM,$FFFF

  ; /* Stuff starting address of point x1,y1 into BLTCPT and BLTDPT
    tmp1.l=bmap+(y1*(320/8))+(2*(x1/16))
    Poke.l #BLTCPT,tmp1
    Poke.l #BLTDPT,tmp1

  ; /* Set up slope in BLTAPT */
    Poke.l #BLTAPT,(4*dmin)-(2*dmax)

  ; /* Byte width goes into BLTCMOD and BLTDMOD */
    Poke.w #BLTCMOD,(320/8)
    Poke.w #BLTDMOD,(320/8)

  ; /* More slopes (All this to draw a bloody LINE!) */
    Poke.w #BLTBMOD,4*dmin
    Poke.w #BLTAMOD,4*(dmin-dmax)

  ; /* Set up line texture $FFFF and line pixel $8000
    Poke.w #BLTBDAT,$FFFF
    Poke.w #BLTADAT,$8000

  ; /* Start blitter operation */
    Poke.w #BLTSIZE,(dmax*64)+66
Return

-----------------------------------------------------
Wiremu Te Kani
E-Mail: tekani@yahoo.com

