@NODE "Mail_106" "Re: Amiga system Libs..."
 for scott@online.u-net.com; Thu, 15 Apr 1999 20:57:25 +0100
From: "David McMinn" <D.Mcminn@eee.rgu.ac.uk>
Organization: The Robert Gordon University, E&EE
Date: Thu, 15 Apr 1999 20:54:59 +0100
encoding: Quoted-printable
Subject: Re: Amiga system Libs...

>    Does anyone know if it is at all possible to create Standard amiga
> libraries in Blitz???  And would they have to be coded in ASM?

 Not actually sure how to write system libs at all, never mind in Blitz, h=
ere's 
what I think you'd need to do:

 Since all your libs have need offsets at the start (I think) then you'd 
obviously have them at the start. Don't know how you'd go about calling th=
em, 
maybe if you done:

libstub1:JMP libfunc1+6(pc) ; probably wrong syntax but thats what you'd w=
ant

libfunc1:
function.l arse(blah)
more blah
end function

 obviously if blitz puts crap at the start of the program then it wouldn't=
 
work, unless you managed to write a correct FD file which got the offset o=
f 
libstub1 correct.

 The +6 is something I found when writing hook stuff, as if you just jump =
the address of libfunc1, it goes tits up. And if you do this, I don't thin=
k the 
debugger likes it (crash-monkey).

 Or it might be a BRA you need instead of the JMP. Or you might need to us=
e a 
dc.w <opcode#> for the BRA/JMP and then dc.l ?libfunc1+6 as Blitz probably=
 
wouldn't compile the ASM properly.


|) /\ \/ ][ |)   |\/| =A9 |\/| ][ |\| |\|
 dmcminn@house-of-mojo.freeserve.co.uk
  http://members.xoom.com/David_McMinn
             ICQ=3D16827694
I'd explain it to you, but your brain would explode.


