@NODE "Mail_112" "Re: Amigalibs.res"
 for scott@online.u-net.com; Tue, 6 Apr 1999 10:57:17 +0100
From: "David McMinn" <D.Mcminn@eee.rgu.ac.uk>
Organization: The Robert Gordon University, E&EE
Date: Tue, 6 Apr 1999 10:55:02 +0100
encoding: Quoted-printable
Subject: Re: Amigalibs.res

> Paul (I think) invented AmigalibsII.res and then Fred created a new
> amigalibs.res with NCS1.70.  That's the one I'm using.

 It was Roger Beausoleil that done the second one.

> The problem is that lots of offsets are not found when trying to
> compile other people's sources.

The problem with that is because Roger tried to avoid tokenisation problem=
s, 
and stuck _'s in front of newtype names, and newtype fields. I think the 
original one, and definately Fred's one, have the same names as the C incl=
udes.

> *SCR/Font/ta_name is one which gives me problems, coz my Font newtype
> doesn't hane anything like a font name or size in it.

Well, I'd suggest you check that you are using the correct thing. In the 
.Screen newtype, there is the Font field, which is a .TextAttr newtype, wh=
ich 
contains the field ta_Name. It really does.

> What am I doing wrong?    Should we standardise on one of these beasts
> when passing code around?   If so, which one?

 We should standardise Fred's one. It has all the includes up to OS3.1 (ne=
ither 
of the others do), and Fred should be releasing a new version soon, as the=
 
unions in the C includes were not converted properly (they're hardly ever =
used 
though). And it keeps the naming convention, unlike Roger's version.


|) /\ \/ ][ |)   |\/| =A9 |\/| ][ |\| |\|
 dmcminn@house-of-mojo.freeserve.co.uk
  http://members.xoom.com/David_McMinn
             ICQ=3D16827694
Tell me what you need, and I'll tell you how to get along without it.


