@NODE "Mail_113" "Re: Amigalibs.res"
 for scott@online.u-net.com; Tue, 6 Apr 1999 20:13:33 +0000
From: Frederic Laboureur <alphasnd@sdv.fr>
Date: Tue, 06 Apr 1999 18:30:46 +0100
Organization: Fantaisie Software
Subject: Re: Amigalibs.res
Encoding: quoted-printable

    Hi Tony, =


> I'm confused about this Amigalibs.res file.   I know what it is and
> what it's for, but there seems to be three of them and I don't know
> which should be used.
> =

> There was one with BlitzII on the original disks and on BSS
> =

> Paul (I think) invented AmigalibsII.res and then Fred created a new
> amigalibs.res with NCS1.70.  That's the one I'm using.
> =

> The problem is that lots of offsets are not found when trying to
> compile other people's sources.    =

> =

> *SCR/Font/ta_name is one which gives me problems, coz my Font newtype
> doesn't hane anything like a font name or size in it.
> =

> What am I doing wrong?    Should we standardise on one of these beasts
> when passing code around?   If so, which one?

    The AmigaLibs.res found in the NCS 1.70 is a try to have a perfect
OS support for the Blitz 2. So you MUST use the the same syntax than
original OS (Old Blitz 2 one was very approximative...). In your
case, you must use the line:

    *SCR\Font\ta_Name
              -> - <-

    It's Case sensitive. By the way you should use the View NewType
function in the menu to show exactly how is the syntax.

    I hope this help,

                        Fred.

