Subject: Re: Amigalibs.res the hungry information super horse

> What newtypes would be commonly used?
> What sort of macros would you have?

 .Window, .Screen, .RastPort - I use these in nearly everything I write. T=
hen 
you've got stuff like .Gadget, .Node, .List, .ExecBase - the list goes on =
and 
on and on. Just take a look at the newtypes from the Compiler menu, when y=
ou 
have entered blitzlibs:amigalibs.res in the resident box in the Compiler 
options. Hundreds of them.

 As for macros, there are a few in the OS includes, but you don't use them=
 as 
