>the inevitable loss of quality and reduction in framerates. Personally
>I would opt for accasional strategic delays to load in chunks of data
>rather than have to reduce the specification. My target is for 25fps
>playback on 030/50 and above in lores working in chunky,

hmmm...320x200?? I assume you mean to a video card...it would depend how
long it`d take for a frame to move from fastram to the video ram...I think
25fps on aga wouldn`t be possible using chunky. A quad speed cd rom (which
is more like what we`d need)....is about 600k/sec. 600k/25 frames = 24k per
frame...without sound...:(

>perhaps
>requiring an 040/25 in order to play 16-bit. Animations really do take
