> then you can watch video cd`s to your hearts content :).

Most of the PC games I've seen atm, seem to use a very low resoloution (low
for PC) format, sometimes with vertical line skips, and audio is usually
played from a CD audio track.

Anyway, what about that format that was developed for Golem?  6x Cd-ROM and
needs only the CHIP mem on a 020 A1200.  It runs about 80mb for a couple of
mins, and it's quit a low resolution as well.

