> method of course is a dump of raw uncompressed data in a solid block
> but then it wouldn't exactly be an animation format so we'd at least
> need to look into delta frames (differences since the last frame).
> Doublebuffering is not a problem as it is with direct-to-chipram
> formats because you can double or triplebuffer the output with no
