It depends on what you mean by "sound" - if you are wanting to synch a music
module with the animation, I think the only feasable method would be to
play the module at the proper speed, and have the animation drop frames if
necessary to keep up with it on slower machines - it would sound pretty
crap to have the music slow down to keep pace with the animation...

If you just want to play sound "effects" at pre-determined points, you could
have a flag included in each animation frame to tell it to play sound #
whatever when this frame is displayed...

