> > There is already a format, I think it's called Wildfire or something
> > like that.. There was a demo of a huge rendered film, with a good
> 
> Do you mean YAFA, Wildfire`s anim format? Then there`s also
> SSA, XFA.

I've had a bit of a look at yafa, it is simply an extension of normal
IFF files, based on the anim7 delta format, with the only differences
being a few extra chunks, data in planar or chunky format, and
possibility to pack the delta data using the xpk system. That somewhat
tells me that it is designed for high storage on disk and not for
being spooled off realtime so doesn't really solve our problem of
playing large anims from cd. I'm pretty sure the xpk compressed data
will not decompress fast enough to be realtime.

-- 
Paul.

