>distinguish (spelling ???)


Umm...everyone seems to be saying software decoding is impossible. You have
to realise that on the pc front, that you buy your machine...use it till
every new piece of software starts running slowly, then upgrade...this is
not amiga land now...big companies do not spend months trying to get their
new unreal clone running on a 486 (A500 for us), they just bang their game
and if it`s slow...you have to upgrade...simple as that (it`s like bintel
saying on their advert you need a PIII to web browse which is ridiculous,
but how else would they sell their tatty new chips!). My friend has a
Celeron
300, and a riva tnt, and we`ve seen it outputing half life to his huge sony
tv
(thanks to a riva tnt and tv output), but it looks horrible...it`s
okay...but it`s
as fuzzy as hell (but we got the refresh rate upto 100 I think)....but my
point is that looks a lot better running at 1280x1024x32@80 on his 17"
monitor.....you have to remember that most tv`s are fairly low res, and
most older tvs have low refresh rates. If your taking about full screen on a
monitor, then your probably talking atleast 1024x768 at 32 bit, which is a
lot of pixels...you couldn`t decode and update that in time (well not unless
you have a very fast cpu or extra hardware). Plus remember that all the new
good graphics cards are coming out with mpeg2 decoding on board
(mg400...not sure about the mg200..but I know of a few others..like ati`s,
diamond viper etc) for when the dvd revolution starts. A voodooII won`t help
you decode mpeg`s in anyway I know of.

I think mpeg`s are great (anything that save disk space is wonderful in my
opinion)...but talking about quality....that`s another matter...I have a tv
tuner card...it`s great...brilliant picture (better than my 21" jvc from a
few years back)...cost me Ł25 ukp from a computer show...captures
avi`s...has teletext, runs at full speed, even in full screen, but when you
click full screen it changes the resolution to the lowest my monitor can
manage....and if I try and drag it to a full sized window on my desktop..it
looks bloody awful. I`m sure a PII 300 could decode mpeg2 at a lower
resolution (ie, closer to your average tv res), you have to realise that you
need a good system to go with it, if you have a slow read device, or low
memory (ie, less than 64mb these days), or a slow graphics card (or a
cheap motherboard/ram etc) then that will contribute towards problems
when decoding stuff like this. I build pc`s for a living, and usually have
design the spec around the uses the person requires it for, and I have
to try and keep upto date and study the latest pc hardware (well, most
