movements than with either of the creative drives, and background blurring
was very much in evidence. The wobble on flat surfaces and shimmering on
edges was not as conspicuos, however, and the subtitles didn`t jerk around
as much as with the other drives we looked at. Overall, the sony DVD-Rom kit
demonstrated slightly better all-round picture quality than it`s peers,
although an obvious jerkiness in picture was occasionally apparent.`


