always seem to support all 3.0 commands correctly (as I suppose the new ones
are quite complicated for the poor pc programmer to understand..plus the
fact that sneaky commodore never properly released the hardware docs...I
wonder why??)...mind you, I always run mine in planar mode...(ie, no gfx
card) so I can play fantastic old games...like millenium2.2, barbarian,
lotus etc..(btw..anybody hear of a game called `Space Ranger`?? where you
had to fly about collecting poor lil critters and saving them from the
baddies...like defender I guess, cos that was one of the first games I
bought for my over priced A500 when it first came out!)...

>So, if someone could try it on both their Amiga and their Amiga Emulator
and
>tell me if it works, and if so how well, I'd really appreciate it.


I`ll give it a go when I get chance...my pc`s hd is pretty full at the
moment (visual c doesn`t help) so I had to move some stuff off it like
winuae...I liked crazy 8`s...used to play it quite a bit....till I tried
changing the card set...and ended up with a card set which included a
horrible screen title across the tops of all the cards :(...

>If you try it, please let me know what emulator you use, and how everything
>compares to the real Amiga system as far as speed, sounds, etc...
>
>I think this information could be helpful to everybody really  (except the
>totally anti-PC folks, anyway...)


Pc`s arent that bad..just the operating system that you run on it ;)


Dave

P.s. I know a few tricks to stop software working on amiga emulators..in
fact...a lot of demos which use undocumented bugs in the hardware to cool
effect do that anyway...but I figured that if people were running my
software...I guess it`s better than people not running my amiga
software...even if it is under false pretenses ;).




