@NODE "Mail_213" "Re: any PC users there?"
 for scott@online.u-net.com; Sun, 11 Apr 1999 18:39:35 +0100
Date: Sun, 11 Apr 1999 16:37:48 +0100
From: Paul Burkey <burkey@bigfoot.com>
X-Accept-Language: en
Subject: Re: any PC users there?
Encoding: 7bit

Andrew Guard wrote:
> > I could mail it if you (or anyone else) wants, but it would make for a
> > rather large attachment - the actual file is about 650k, and attaching it
> > to a mail would make for over 800k I would think.
>
> Nope a lot biger then that.  256 <> 64 would make 650K in to 1950K.
> Simple realy 100K File size in a E-Mail in 300K.  The mathes if you
> haven't work it out are 1==3

I don`t know what kind of attachment encoding you use but I think you
should change it. a 100k file would be about 138k and a 650k file
would become almost 900k. Encoding a binary is just a case of taking
a strip of 8 bit data and spreading it through a strip of 7bit
characters. That would result in something around 1.35 times bigger
depending on how much extra info is used ie, error checking etc.

Cheers,

Paul

