I watched as Andrew Guard hammered "Re: any PC users there?" out on their
keyboard...

> This would be intresting information.  I looking at from view point
> that system should declare what is because I belive the system
> shouldn't hide it self. Persional I beleve that PC sould declare them
> selves as 070 etc.

Not actually possible seeing as exec.library only provides a single byte for
the processor, the maximum of which is 060.

Anyways, there are ways: Draco systems have an extra resource, called oddly
enough "draco.resource" and I think that UAE loads a special filesystem, so
you'd just have to check for that.

