--BOUNDARY.1748070152.7

Neil Bullock churned out *this* drivel:

> Can someone explain to me how exactly you can get Appwindows and Appicons
> open and how you can read input into them?

Here's a little bit of demo code...cant remember what library the commands
were from though...

See ya,
-- 
<tsb>
<sb>James L Boyd - jamesboyd@all-hail.freeserve.co.uk
<sb>Member of Team *AMIGA*, and *Dogbert's New Ruling Class.*
<sb>Connected from Dundee, Scotland. 
<sb>(http://surf.to/all-hail/)
<tsb>

Good morning, doctors. I have taken the liberty of removing 
Windows 95 from my hard drive.
-- HAL's first words contest winner, judged by Arthur C. Clarke.

--BOUNDARY.1748070152.7
Content-Disposition: attachment; filename="AppTrials.asc"
Encoding: quoted-printable
Content-Description: AppIcons & AppWindows

WBenchToFront_

FindScreen 0

NoCli

Window 0,150,50,250,150,$140f,"",1,2

wres.l=3DAddAppWindow (0)

If wres=3D0 Then Request "Error","Couldn't create appwindow","OK":End

ires.l=3DAddAppIcon (0,"Test Icon","sys:utilities/multiview")

If ires=3D0
  Request "Error","AppIcon Failed","OK"
EndIf

=2Eloop

Repeat

VWait

If Event=3D$200 Then Goto quit
Until AppEvent

WLocate 0,5

atype=3DAppEventType
anum=3DAppNumFiles

If atype=3D2 AND AppNumFiles=3D0 Then Request "","We have a double-click!=
","END":Goto quit

NPrint "Event type: ",atype
NPrint "AppNumFiles: ",anum

  For a=3D1 To anum

    a$=3DAppFile(a)
                                                                         =
                                                   ffff
    NPrint "AppEventType : ",atype:NPrint""
    NPrint "AppFile : ",a," : ",a$

    If Right$(a$,3)=3D"txt" Then Execute_ "c:ppmore "+a$,0,0

  Next a

MouseWait

WCls

Goto loop

=2Equit
If wres Then DelAppWindow (0)
If ires Then DelAppIcon (0)
End


--BOUNDARY.1748070152.7

