From: Anton Reinauer <anton@ww.co.nz>
Date: Fri, 16 Apr 1999 10:29:49 +1200
Subject: Audio compression
Encoding: quoted-printable

On 16-Apr-99, Sami N=E4=E4t=E4nen wrote:
  =

> Well I have the sample compressor and decompressor. In fact it can use
> new exponential delta too, which in fact gives beter sound quality in
> 8 bit sounds. So the idea of the coding is that every byte from the
> sample is replaced by one nible, and this nible tells which value from
> the table of -128 -64 -32 -16 -8 -4 -2 -1 0 1 2 4 8 16 32 64 you will
> add to the previous sample value (Fibonachi coding uses fibonachi
> numbers instead of power of 2's) This packing method halves the needed
> space for samples.

  So you're losing accuracy to get better compression, the same as
converting 16 bit samples down to 8 bit- instead you're converting 8
bit samples down to 4 bit- any idea what quality is like? =

  Also this simplifying down of the sample would make it easier for a
repetitive routine to work on it! That is how AI (speech recognition
etc) works anyhow. =


-- =

        Anton Reinauer <anton@ww.co.nz>
     =



