From: Curt Esser <camge@ix.netcom.com>
Date: Tue, 27 Apr 1999 07:16:58 -0500
Subject: Re: Bad Email programs

Hi David

On 27-Apr-99, David McMinn wrote:
>> outlook express could delete them from the pop3 server. I`m not naming
>> any names (David McMinn...lol), but it`s due to a BAD email send. What
>> happen

I don't suppose this could be one of those "innocent mistakes" Microsoft
makes to try to force everybody to use their software?

Your mails come in fine here, David.  And on everybody else's system too,
I'm sure, or you would have heard about it long ago...

Later...
