@NODE "Mail_255" "Re: Bad Email programs (Was Re: Pinball algorithms)"
 for scott@online.u-net.com; Tue, 27 Apr 1999 04:28:27 +0100
From: "Dave" <dave@nbsamiga.demon.co.uk>
Subject: Re: Bad Email programs (Was Re: Pinball algorithms)
Date: Tue, 27 Apr 1999 04:27:47 +0100
	charset="iso-8859-1"
Encoding: 7bit


>Hello ppl, just a note to say hello - I joined the list about 5 days ago,
>but have only just managed to get Outlook Express on this PC to download
all
>my mail - kept hanging on one message - which meant I kept getting the same
>mail over and over.

Hi Victor,

 Welcome to the list. I too have been stuck downloading, first 25, then 54,
then 74 of the same emails about 5/6 times, and then only to crash before
outlook express could delete them from the pop3 server. I`m not naming any
names (David McMinn...lol), but it`s due to a BAD email send. What happen is
that the marvelous program david was using thinks it`s okay to do
<CRLF>.<CRLF> because there was only a single dot on a line. What the
program should have done is to add another . (to make <CRLF>..<CRLF>) which
would have been removed automatically by the receiving program.....how do I
know this, and the creators of Pegasus not?? Cos I read RFC 821...a long
long while ago..anyway, here`s what it says....

             The mail data is terminated by a line containing only a
            period, that is the character sequence "<CRLF>.<CRLF>" (see
            Section 4.5.2 on Transparency).  This is the end of mail
            data indication.

My advice...check for updates of pegasus with that fixed, or use something
better ;) (it`s not davids fault..but if he should ever do it again...I know
of a voodoo doll site...which we can all stick pins in a david mcminn
doll...hehehe)


>I was working on a game called George II, but have put it to one side, as
>I`ve just played Kirby`s pinball on a GameBoy emulator, and fancy doing a
>version in Blitz.


Cool..I loved kirby ;)


>1.  Does anyone know where I should look for appropriate algorithms for
>bouncing pinballs - or do I have to work one out myself using trial and
>error?


Hmmm...do you know any C...because there are lots of sites with C (maybe
some pascal too) examples for this sort of thing (well everything
really...from 2d to 3d and back!).


>I`m using my sister`s email account, as I can`t figure out how to set a new
>one up with Explorer - but my name is Victor Bell


You have to add another email account (tools menu), and then select which
acount you want to use by selecting it in the same menu (ie, to set your
current address for outgoing emails).


>Look forward to any replies
>
>VICTOR BELL
>
>Hope I`ve sent this to the right place
>


Yes...this is the right place :).....

Dave



