@NODE "Mail_260" "Re: Basic Trig"
 for scott@online.u-net.com; Sun, 18 Apr 1999 17:56:37 +0100
From: "Dave" <dave@nbsamiga.demon.co.uk>
Subject: Re: Basic Trig
Date: Sun, 18 Apr 1999 17:24:48 +0100
	charset="iso-8859-1"
Encoding: 7bit

>Hi Everyone,


Hi Liz,

>There is a command in Blitz called QAngle which returns the angle between 2
>2D points. However it appears to return the wrong values. It says it
returns
>between 0 and 1 with 1=360deg. However with 2 points in a vertical line I
>should get 0.5 returned which would equate to 180deg but I am getting
around
>0.2 being returned. Therefore can someone remind me of the trig formulas
for
>working out the angle 'by hand'.


I think it`s the inverse tan of (dy/dx)

In blitz I use

dx=x2-x1        (x2 should always be greater)
dy=y2-y1        (y2 should always be greater)
radtodeg=180.0/pi            (I think)

Atan(dy/dx)*radtodeg

should give you 0 to 360...watch out when dx=0 though, and negative dx/dy
numbers


Though I`m not sure..I used that in my mario kart game, and it seems to
work....

Dave




