>And my Re:Trig :)

Actually, I just checked my program, and I think atan(dy/dx) only returns
0-90 degrees, so then you need to know the quadrant your x2,x1 is...ie

                    90
                      !
           *          !
180 ------------*-----------  0
                       !
                       !
                     270

I used atan(abs(dy)/abs(dx)) and then checked the sgn of dx and dy with a
series of if..else..endif statements to see which quadrant it was in and
then rotated the angle depening on the quater it was in (ie, dx=-1,dy=-1
then angle=angle+90). I hope that`s right...though I`m probably doing
something wrong...but not matter what dy/dx I did, I always got values
between 0 & 90 (isn`t that because it`s a right angle triangle??). Actually,
for some reason on two of the quadrants I swapped dy with dx....something to
do with translation I seem to remember.....(ie, I tested for the quadrant
before doing the atan thing). (but maybe thats because in my floor mapping,
0 degress is down, and not right!)...been a long while since I wrote that
code though....

Dave


