Hello Again,

 Anybody have an idea what the best 24 bit image format is....I need it to
be fairly simply, and don`t want to many different compression
routines....I`ve checked out tagra, Tiff, iff, bmp, gif, png and some
obscure ones...what I really need is something that a lot of programs
support (so I can swap other formats to this), and it has to be chunky
(well, one byte each for R,G,B for the each pixel).....I thought tagra might
have been best, but it seems to have too many silly (and similar)
compression chunks.....at the moment I`m looking a bmp (ummm...windows
rubbish...but it has a simple 24 bit format, and simply compression...what
else do you expect from ms....)

Any ideas?? As I`ll be needing atleast 450 seperate frames for 30 seconds
(agahghhhhh)...and the only other option is to write a avi converter
(nightmare time).......(450 frames is about 98MB to you, which I need to
squeeze to 2.9MB...hohoho)...and I`m expecting it to take upto 3 minutes per
frame to encode (using a crappy slow badly written encode..maybe I`ll be
able speed it up to 2 minutes later on...woohoo)....that`s about 22.5 hours
of encoding for a 30 second video.......ack...so you can see why a I need a
decent image format!

Dave



