How about storing each frame as a 256 color GIF with
(potentially) a unique palette. That'll save you a
bucket-load of space in exchange for a loss of quality.
You'll have to decide whether the (not-too-large)
loss of quality brought on by going down to 256 colors
per frame is acceptable to you or not.

Dobbin

