@NODE "Mail_267" "BFB Sussed ;))"
 for scott@online.u-net.com; Fri, 23 Apr 1999 22:56:21 +0100
From: Rob Hutchinson <loki@napalmdeath.freeserve.co.uk>
Date: Fri, 23 Apr 1999 22:50:25 +0100
Organization: Satanic Dreams Software.
Subject: BFB Sussed ;))

Hello,

   Ok thaks to everyone for testing the SDSBFBPlayer lib,.. ta v.much ;)

I think I have sussed what is causing the enforcer hits,.. and it`s my fault
not the lib, or the way we converted it ;).. It`s just cos I was doing
constant checks on module info that wasn`t always there,.. IE, if you kick
up the program first time, you get enforcer hits cos it`s checking
non-assigned mem ;))).. Now if you load one in, the enforcer hits stop!,
This is because the mem is now assigned (BFBLoadModule{}).. If you stop
the module, the enforcer hits dont come back.. This is because the module
structure still exists. If you free the module, the module info is nuked
and the enforcer hits come back (this is just a hypothesis, but I`m pretty
sure it`s correct)... In which case, it`s my stupid fault for not realising
when I did it ;).. It just means that you setup a flag when you load
a module instead of using BFBModLoaded{} (Which is the nasty proc
causing all the enforcer hits ;) (I think)).. It`s as simple as that ;)..
I might do a quick update later on which will set say, modloaded.b to
true or false when loading and freeing modules. (same goes with playing
and the others ;)).. Thats all it needs ;)

Oh yeah, and Amorel, this is the BFB library, thats why those useless module
formats are supported.. It`s because that is how BFB is, but for anyone
who wants to support some of these obscure module formats in a multi-module-
format player then BFB will come in handy.. If not, and if you were just
using it for say MOD or MED, then it`s still nice cos it makes the EXE
smaller, and you just distribute the required sublib ;) simple..
Also the reason I just made it drag`n`drop cos I only wrote it in the first 
place as an example to go with the conversion to serve as a starting-point ;)
(not that it`s hard to use the conversion or anything, though the sample
 lists setup might have needed a LITTLE explaining ;))

Again, thanks y`all ;)

Cya!
-- 
