@NODE "Mail_270" "Re: Bitmap output"
 for scott@online.u-net.com; Sun, 18 Apr 1999 17:04:50 +0000
From: "David McMinn" <D.Mcminn@eee.rgu.ac.uk>
Organization: The Robert Gordon University, E&EE
Date: Sun, 18 Apr 1999 17:02:53 +0100
encoding: Quoted-printable
Subject: Re: Bitmap output



<color><param>7F00,0000,0000</param>> The Blitz mamual says that you can o=
nly use "up to 8x8 fixed fonts"

> for output to a bitmap.

> 

> Is this a Blitz restriction or a real Amiga one?    Any workarounds

> please?


 Blitz. It sucks. And its only 8x8, nothing else. However:


------------

<color><param>0100,0100,0100</param>; This needs amigalibs.res

WbToScreen 0

Window 0,0,0,640,256,$100f,"hh",-1,-1


; Prints text to an x and y position on the currently used

; bitmap, in the currently used font.

Statement BPrint{a$,x.w,s.w,y.w,col.l}

    DEFTYPE.RastPort rp

    InitRastPort_ &rp

    rp\BitMap =3D Addr BitMap(Used BitMap)

    SetFont_ &rp,Peek.l(Addr IntuiFont(Used IntuiFont)+8)


    ; Move to correct position, unfortunately you need to keep

    ; track of the position yourself, unlike with Print & NPrint

    ; Should be easy though, y position increases by the font

    ; height, x position increases by TextLength_(&rp,&a$,Len(a$))

    Move_ &rp,x,y

    SetAPen_ &rp,col

    Text_ &rp,&a$,Len(a$)

End Statement


; Load font and set up bitmap. These will also become the currently

; used ones, but you could also change it by doing:

; Use Bitmap x or Use IntuiFont y

LoadFont 0,"helvetica.font",24

BitMap 0,320,200,3


BPrint{"blah blah",100,0,20,3}

BitMaptoWindow 0,0,0,0,WLeftOff,WTopOff,320,200

While WaitEvent<<>$200:Wend

End

-----------


 I had to put the extra s.w parameter in, because the acidlibs file I have=
 here 
is broken (third parameter is screwed in some functions, that have newtype=
s 
bigger than a long - in this case the rastport). Anyone wanting a fix for =
this, 
che<color><param>0000,0000,0000</param>ck out http://www.a2points.com/home=
page/3698138/libs/AcidLibs.fix by Julian 
Kinraid.



<nofill>
