{code snipped}

Excellent!  I have wanted to print to bitmaps with standard fonts for ages,
as FNS fonts don't support the "alternate" characters.

I just wanted to add that you can also use the command:

SetDrMd_ &rp,(drawmode)  in the function, to control the "Jam Mode" of the
printing.

The drawmode uses the same parameters as the Blitz "WJam" command:

0 = Text printed with transparent background
1 = Text printed on rectangle of background colour
2 = Text XOR'd onto the bitmap
4 = Text Inversed 

etc... 
 

                                    Yours electronically,
