    Hi Paul, =


>> ii) Problems with Programs.  I have a program that when I Compile/Run =
it
>> works fine.  If I then 'Run' it again, I get a 'Trap 0' error, and Bli=
tz
>> crashes, requiring a reset.  but, if I Compile/Run it instead, it work=
s
>> fine. Any ideas ? I can't think of a reason there would be for this.
>> The only thing I've been using of late is  Allocmem_  .  But I Freemem=
_
>> them before the end of program.
>> Oh, maybe Mildred is the problem.....
> =

> Possibly Mildred. At least, the same seems to happen for most people.
> Although it is perfectly feasible to make an exe file and run it any
> number of times without problems, blitz doesn't seem to like running
> after it's been compiled and run already.

    I've had the problem before with the GadTools lib of the NCS. It's
because when you run the program a second time (without recompiling)
the 'global bank' of your library (here MildRed) isn't flushed, so
you're checks to see if something is already loaded fails and the
GURU come... I've fixed that by doing a little loop which flush
the bank, before start. I hope this help,

    Bye,

                        Fred.

