@NODE "Mail_282" "Re: Blitz ???"
 for scott@online.u-net.com; Wed, 7 Apr 1999 00:50:33 +0000
From: amorel <amorel@xs4all.nl>
Date: Tue, 06 Apr 1999 17:06:01 +0500
Subject: Re: Blitz ???

On 05-Apr-99, BaH wrote:

C=Now for some questions-

C=i)  Playing Mods from Fast Ram.  Is it possible ?  Or should I forget about
C=that and just load them when I need them ?

Of course it is possible. I personally havent bothered to code my own engine,
but if you play mmdx songs via the octamed libraries you can play them either
from chip or fast mem. Check some octamed dev docs on aminet. Playing
digibooster songs also goes through fastmem(if available) and so does any
stuff going through ahi.

Browse through some kernel manuals for more info, if you wanna code an engine
yourself, I`d say.

-- 
