@NODE "Mail_300" "Re: Blitz Mailing list 2000"
 for scott@online.u-net.com; Fri, 2 Apr 1999 00:54:24 +0100
From: Anton Reinauer <anton@ww.co.nz>
Date: Fri, 02 Apr 1999 11:45:53 +1200
Subject: Re: Blitz Mailing list 2000

On 01-Apr-99, Rob Hutchinson wrote:
> Hello,
> 
>   Ok, now we have admin (we dont we?), there isn`t a lot of point in
> the second list (I agree)?? Unless we are going to have an Expert and
> beginners list (which I think is a cool idea, as those new to
> programming/blitz dont want to get 40 emails with stuff that is just
> way too complicated, and they just chuck it in the bin)?
> 
> So what should happen to BML2?.. As getting the experts to all switch
> is a pain, what about renaming it to BBB (Blitz Basic Begginners) or
> something like that maybe?.. Then the newbies can start on the `new'
> list and only those `experts' who WANT to help the newbies with their
> problems need join the `new' list??
 
  Probably not a bad idea, but I think most experts wouldn't probably
bother- if it's one list they'll still lend a hand when needed. Also
it's worth having the high powered stuff around, as there's so much you
need to learn these day- a good thing for beginners to do would be to
keep the mails or attachments as a resource for later on, so they can
tackle it later when they need it.

-- 
        Anton Reinauer <anton@ww.co.nz>
      


