> > something like that maybe?.. Then the newbies can start on the `new'
> > list and only those `experts' who WANT to help the newbies with their
> > problems need join the `new' list??
>  
>   Probably not a bad idea, but I think most experts wouldn't probably
> bother- if it's one list they'll still lend a hand when needed. Also
> it's worth having the high powered stuff around, as there's so much you
> need to learn these day- a good thing for beginners to do would be to
> keep the mails or attachments as a resource for later on, so they can
> tackle it later when they need it.

The problem is that (almost) everyone is a beginner at something, and
most of us are experts at something else.    I really think that
having just a single list is by far the best idea.  I've learnt heaps
by reading code I didn't understand.

Cheers

-- 
Tony Rolfe
