Yep, the worse thing about this lib is the fact that the argument parsing
is knackered!!!.. But the other commands are shagged too... the update fixes
the argument parsing, but cocks up the RXRunScript (incidently, try using
this over RXExecuteScript).. Or you could try:

  C:Run >NIL: SYS:REXXc/Rx >CON: <FILE>

But this will not use the Blitz console.. and the output it does open will
be closed directly after use.. which MAY be a good thing?

According to my m8, the bodgeup is because of some old OS2 hooks that
are used in the libs.. 

[=> Can anyone help?

me me..,..

Hope this helps ;)

