@NODE "Mail_335" "BlitzListAdmin"
 for scott@online.u-net.com; Fri, 23 Apr 1999 17:38:48 +0100
From: Donovan Reeve <bubby.lnk@ispi.net>
Date: Fri, 23 Apr 1999 10:30:25 +0500
Subject: BlitzListAdmin

Hi all,

  On April 6, 1999 the following message was posted to this list:



>  Not one single person voted against the idea of having remote
administrators
>for the list but not moderators.  Because this idea was specifically allowed
>and even encouraged by the system administrater there are no roadblocks from
>that quarter.  Therefor, by common consent and vote, we now have on this list
>provision for remote administrators (3 has been suggested as a good number)
>but we will remain self-moderated.
>
>  In view of the above results, it is time to finish the process by getting
>the list of canadates.  I propose that if there are three or less canadates
>and no one objects to any of them that we simply have another vote of
>"abstainance" where only desenting votes are registered and everybody else is
>considered as having voted "for".
>
>  So now we need volunteers (canadates).  I have seen two already, but please
>resubmit your names at this time so we can all be sure where we stand.
>
>  We will (unless someone objects) allow till the 15th of April (1999) for
>people to volunteer, upon which we will have discussion allowed for as
>short of a period as is needed to narrow the field if needed, and then
>a voting period.
>
>  Volunteers please remember that you need the following qualifications:
>
>  Time to monitor the list regularly
>
>  A reliable internet connection
>
>  A good working knowledge of the list and its operations
>
>
>
>  Volunteers?...



  The following people responded to this message by volunteering for the
task of acting as remote administrators of this list (to be working under
the jurisdiction of the regular administrator):

  Rob Hutchinson

  Rui Carvalho


  Both have qualifications which would indicate that they can handle the job.



  One other person had shown interest before, but did not respond to this
call for action.  If you are still interested, please message the list at
this time (before April 28) to indicate so.


  We will now allow a short period (until May 1) for any discussion of these
names, at which time if there are no objections a voting period of one week
(ending at midnight GST between May 7 and May 8) will commense.

  If there are any serious objections to any of the names, an anouncement
will be made concerning the plans for resolution of the situation.

  If no serious objections are made to the canidates, then the voting period
will commense as scheduled and will again be a vote of abstainance, meaning
that the silence of any list member is counted as a vote in favor, and only
those wishing to vote against will message the list with their vote.

  If the number voting against is not clearly a significant portion of the
list subscribers then the canadates will be considered to have been approved
by the majority.

  If there are enough who vote against to raise the question of whether
they are approaching or surpassing 50% of the list subscribers, then the
list administrator will be asked to indicate what the current number of
subscribers is so a calculation of majority can be made.



  The discussion till May 1 should include the following subjects:

-  Is there any objection to any of the persons listed as far as their
sutibility for the position of remote list administrators of this list.

-  If objections are raised, is there any affirmation of ability or
suitability which would bear on, negate or contridict the objection(s).

-  The following is a list of the assumed responcibilities and performance
for remote list administrators so that we are all clear on what to expect.
These may be discussed if necesissary also.


  Aid list users with list-related problems such as unsubscribing dificulty.

  Protect the list from spammers and blatant, offensive flaming by outsiders.

  Removing abandoned subscriptions.

  Alerting the main list administration of problems with list distribution,
  subscribing or other matters requiring possible action at the main sight.




Remote administrators MUST NOT


  Remove or interfere with any account on the list which is not abandoned.

  Attempt to moderate discussion in an official way (although like everyone
else they will certainly be allowed to freely express their personal
oppinions including objecting to off-topic or slanderous content if they
wish).  This is because we have voted to remain a self-moderated list,
meaning that the only moderating action which will take place will be the
messaging of approval, dissaproval, agreement, dissagreement, suggestions
and (hopefully kindly) flames by the list subscribers.  If a person on the
list is being obnoxious to the point of it amounting to spamming and many
of the list users are indicating that they are tired of it, the remote
administrators may wish to poll the list as to whether any official action
should be taken.  The will of the list users will be law in the area of
moderation as long as it is the policy of the list owner to allow us to
be self-moderated.




  O.K.   Discussion?






Donovan Reeve (bubby.lnk@ispi.net)



