>> 
>> 
>>   Both have qualifications which would indicate that they can handle the
>job.
>> 
>> 
>> 
>>   One other person had shown interest before, but did not respond to this
>> call for action.  If you are still interested, please message the list at
>> this time (before April 28) to indicate so.
>> 

>It was probobly me. I just have one problem. I wont be able to read e-mails
>everyday during summer. I am away from uni from the beginning of June
>until the end of August.

>I guess you have to decide if I can apply anyway.


  Well, it's not really up to me, I am just acting as a temp to get this
thing rolling and settled.  It's really up to the people on this list and
the main list administrator.  I wouldn't think we would expect the remote
administrators to read the list every day though.  I would suggest that
a minimum of once a week and preferably twice a week be required with the
expectation of the occasional miss (for vacation etc.).  After all, that's
why we are looking for three remote administrators, so hopefully there
will allways be one around when needed.

I suggest the following guidelines:

  Each remote administrator message the list when he/she is going to be
absent for as long as a week or more and try to ascertain that there
will be at least one remote administrator present while he/she is gone.

  Each remote administrator message the list and the other administrators
if they plan to relenquish the post of remote administrator or quit the list.
Preferably then the remaining remote administrators would ask for volunteers
and hold an election to replace the one who is leaving.




  So, Anders.  I propose that you be accepted under those conditions if you
are willing and able.  Please message the list with a yes or no.

  Any opposed speak up.

  Any with additional ideas or questions, open a discussion please.


Donovan Reeve (bubby.lnk@ispi.net)



