> 	If i used Mildred for some of the 2d graphic stuff (because there
> would be isometric stuff n'all) how quickly could a full screen backdrop be
> refreshed (i.e. copying the chunky pic back to the screen) or would it be
> best to write some sort of buffer type thing - which I can see being good fr
> small polys but when characters walk right up to the camera it could get
> nasty. The advantage of full screen refresh is that the backdrops could be
> fully animated. Please don't send me responses about too mucbh memory use
> blah blah I am aware of this I just want to try some ideas.
> 	Does anyone have any Polyf commands that work in conjunction with
> mildred or does mildred now have these commands?
> 	thanks  ppl

It depends on the cpu. It is possible on an 040/25 to do MBlockScroll
of a 320x200 area about *5* times while c2p'ing also at 25fps.

There is no polygon commands in Mildred, although you can do a kind of
polyline (unfilled) using MLine.

I only really know about how the blitter fills polygons and only then
how to do it in planar to get different colours. I've never done a
polygon scanline rendered thingy so perhaps someone else can come up
with something.

-- 
Paul.

