@NODE "Mail_348" "Re: Byte-aligning"
 for scott@online.u-net.com; Sat, 17 Apr 1999 16:24:33 +0100
From: Damir Arh <damir.arh@guest.arnes.si>
Date: Sat, 17 Apr 1999 17:16:55 +0100
Subject: Re: Byte-aligning

Hello everyone

On 06-Jan-78, James L Boyd shared his opinion:

> I have to turn a value into the next "divisible-by-4" value available,
> and I've written this little routine, but does anyone see a quicker
> way to do it?

Maybe something like that:

r = l mod 4
l = l + 4 - r

This should change l to the correct value.


Kind regards from Slovenia
-- 
Damir Arh <damir.arh@guest.arnes.si>
