@NODE "Mail_349" "Re: Byte-aligning"
 for scott@online.u-net.com; Sat, 17 Apr 1999 18:09:03 +0100
From: "Paul" <paulwest@stationone.demon.co.uk>
Organization: private
Date: 17 Apr 99 18:07:59 +0000
Subject: Re: Byte-aligning
Encoding: 7bit

> Hi all, 
> 
> I have to turn a value into the next "divisible-by-4" value available,
> and I've written this little routine, but does anyone see a quicker
> way to do it?
 
Print "Enter a value between 0 and 99 : "
 
l=Edit(2)                         ; user input into function

NPrint "Original value given : ",l

l AND $FFFFFFFC

NPrint "Truncated value : ",l

-- 
Paul.

