@NODE "Mail_350" "Re: Byte-aligning"
 for scott@online.u-net.com; Sat, 17 Apr 1999 18:16:18 +0000
From: Sami =?iso-8859-1?Q?N=E4=E4t=E4nen?= <sami.naatanen@dlc.fi>
Date: Sat, 17 Apr 1999 19:13:00 +0300
Subject: Re: Byte-aligning
Encoding: quoted-printable

On 06-Jan-78, James L Boyd wrote.

>  Hi all, =

>  =

>  I have to turn a value into the next "divisible-by-4" value available,=

>  and I've written this little routine, but does anyone see a quicker
>  way to do it?
>  =

>  See ya,

Very easy!

newl=3D(l+3)&$fffffffc

will give the next possible value divisible with 4 (if the current value =
is
not divisible with it)

