@NODE "Mail_355" "Re: Catalogues (fwd)"
 for scott@online.u-net.com; Wed, 21 Apr 1999 14:26:20 +0000
From: James L Boyd <jamesboyd@all-hail.freeserve.co.uk>
Date: Wed, 21 Apr 1999 14:21:22 +0000
Subject: Re: Catalogues (fwd)

--BOUNDARY.1748036968.1

[this was meant just for Rob Huchinson, but since a few people have
mentioned it, I'll post it to the list - this is just my own experience with
using Locale...]

> I meant to send this to the list, but messed up and sent it direct, so of
> course you never saw it...

> [=> Not exactly built-in, but it's fairly simple to do. James Boyd did a
> set [=> of functions to use Locale cataloges for BeatBox2. I could send
> 'em to [=> you, if it's OK with him. But he could explain 'em much better
> than I [=> could.

Well, they're not mine actually...but I can't remember where I got them
from...

IM-not-so-HO, forget about using catalogs - they are a massive (MASSIIIIVE!)
pain in the arse to deal with...most catalog creation programs are bugged
beyond belief, you have to keep going into another language to test your
created catalogs (which usually don't work), and you have to keep rebooting to
flush 'em out before testing updated versions, then there's the hassle of
adding more strings to your program and having to keep editing your catalogs,
plus users who find they can't do conversions of your catalog because they're
bugged (thanks to whatever program you used), and so on...

As you can see, I'm no longer a fan ;)

If you want foreign language support, I'd recommend a DIY approach (doesn't
look as cool, but saves all the above) :

Just an ascii file for each language, with numbered strings would do. Your
user selects a language and your program loads the ascii strings into an array.

I've attached a little function which would let you select a language file
automatically too...

Also, this would work on any system, not just OS2.0+ (?)...

If you are some kind of weird masochist, try ReCatItPro or UCT from Aminet...

Hope this helps,
-- 
<tsb>
<sb>James L Boyd - jamesboyd@all-hail.freeserve.co.uk
<sb>Member of Team *AMIGA*, and *Dogbert's New Ruling Class.*
<sb>Connected from Dundee, Scotland. 
<sb>(http://surf.to/all-hail/)
<tsb>

There are two kinds of people, those who finish what they start and 
so on...
-- Robert Byrne

--BOUNDARY.1748036968.1
Content-Disposition: attachment; filename="GetLanguage.asc"
Content-Description: Returns language used on system

Function$ Language {}

  l$="locale.library"
  *loclib=OpenLibrary_ (&l$,0)

  If *loclib

    *locale.Locale=OpenLocale_(0)

    If *locale
      country$=Peek$(*locale\loc_LanguageName)
      CloseLocale_ *locale
    EndIf

  CloseLibrary_ *loclib
  EndIf

  If country$
    country$=Left$(country$,Len(country$)-9)
  EndIf

Function Return country$
End Function

; demo :

NPrint Language {}

MouseWait:End


--BOUNDARY.1748036968.1

