@NODE "Mail_360" "Re: Chunky anims"
 for scott@online.u-net.com; Tue, 13 Apr 1999 22:46:50 +0000
From: "Paul" <paulwest@stationone.demon.co.uk>
Organization: private
Date: 13 Apr 99 22:45:24 +0000
Subject: Re: Chunky anims
Encoding: 7bit

Andreas,

> Well on the subject of animation support for mildred. I'm wondering
> if it would be possible to play a 640*320 (256cols of course) anim,
> that plays from a 4xCD (mimum specs or perhaps even 8xCD),
> on a gfxcard equiped machine, with 030+ and 4mb of ram
> with a decent playback speed?

Maybe. I guess we'll find out soon.

I'm not sure if it will end up as part of mildred or not tho, but
possible, as it would be interesting to get easy access to an anim for
using with other commands (like transparent playback or something).

> Now after having asked that, and if the answer my question is yes,
> then would it be possible to play the anim and at cdda music
> file with the anim as well.

No. At least, I don't think so. I assume that CDDA hogs the cdrom. If
it doesn't then maybe it would be possible.

> Now I will settle (heh perhaps this is the high end method) of playing
> a cdda track next to the anim. I think a 4x would give me 600kb/s
> transfer possibilty and a 8x would give me 1200kb/s transfer
> rate of the cd.

That's without pausing to decompress or anything like that.
 
> I also know that mildred is a fast system for scrolling etc, but I have
> no idea which speeds you may get when using chunky anims with it.

As I said we'll find out soon. It doesn't look too bad so far,
although compression time is horrendous in blitz code.

> Ohh yeah.I'm willing to use as much asm as needed (even routines
> optimised for a special setup). Ohh yeah...if someone will strech as
> for as doing test which will give framerate feedback then it would be
> great, but i'm not asking anyoe to write my routines. Just need to know
> if it can be done, and at what results...

It would certainly need to go into asm to do any decompression nice
and quick and be optimised as much as possible. I think your
requirements can possibly be met at 15fps, but i dont know how fast
the cdrom would have to be to do so, or if an 030 cpu is enough.

-- 
Paul.

