@NODE "Mail_362" "Re: Chunky anims"
 for scott@online.u-net.com; Wed, 14 Apr 1999 02:12:56 +0100
Date: Wed, 14 Apr 1999 00:46:25 +0100
From: Paul Burkey <burkey@bigfoot.com>
X-Accept-Language: en
Subject: Re: Chunky anims
Encoding: quoted-printable

"Andreas H=E5kansson" wrote:
> Well on the subject of animation support for mildred. I'm wondering
> if it would be possible to play a 640*320 (256cols of course) anim,
> that plays from a 4xCD (mimum specs or perhaps even 8xCD),
> on a gfxcard equiped machine, with 030+ and 4mb of ram
> with a decent playback speed?

That might be possible but it's pushing the limits of 030 and 4X CD.
To compress the data enough to provide good speed and small data size
you would need to use a heavy compression such as the kind used in
most AVI's and QT's.

> Of course the anim would have to be using delta frames etc to
> reduce the size of the anim, and increas eth playback fps. I'm
> hoping to land on about 15fps (higher if possible). I can
> actually even strech the memory up to 8mb of that helps.

You could do with with just 2Meg of fast ram. You only need enough
memory to load and build the anim frame. That is unless your anim
only has a small number of frames and you want to pre-load it all
into ram first! :)

> Now after having asked that, and if the answer my question is yes,
> then would it be possible to play the anim and at cdda music
> file with the anim as well. Or perhaps cdda wouldnt me the optimal
> approce...perhaps an integrated format with both gfx and sound
> to enable keyframe controle to sync the music and anim perfectly.

Play CDDA while you`re parsing the anim from CD? Impossible. You
could install the anim to HD and then play CDDA but I presume you
didn`t mean this because you mentioned 4x and 8x CD's which wouldn`t
be an issue if you`re parsing from HD.

Cheers,

Paul

-- =

< Paul Burkey http://www.sneech.freeserve.co.uk >



