@NODE "Mail_363" "Re: Chunky anims"
 for scott@online.u-net.com; Thu, 15 Apr 1999 19:33:56 +0100
From: Rick Hodger <rick.thehub@bigfoot.com>
Date: Wed, 14 Apr 1999 20:09:27 +0100
Organization: Pagan Software
Subject: Re: Chunky anims

I watched as Paul hammered "Re: Chunky anims" out on their keyboard...

>> Now after having asked that, and if the answer my question is yes,
>> then would it be possible to play the anim and at cdda music
>> file with the anim as well.

> No. At least, I don't think so. I assume that CDDA hogs the cdrom. If
> it doesn't then maybe it would be possible.

If you did use CDDA, then you wouldn't be able to stream from a CD.  Reading
data forces the laser from reading the music track to reading the data
track.

> It would certainly need to go into asm to do any decompression nice
> and quick and be optimised as much as possible. I think your
> requirements can possibly be met at 15fps, but i dont know how fast
> the cdrom would have to be to do so, or if an 030 cpu is enough.

Actually using CDDA, you have little or no system overheads, but it does
mean that unless you are willing to interrupt your audio, you can't read
from the CD-ROM.

-- 
