Subject: Code

--=_=8<==MD2370912B4-519E69F7==8<=_=
Encoding: 8bit

Hi all,

today I wrote a little tool which (hopefully makes the life a little
easier. 

I uplaoded it to Aminet today 

-----------------------------------snip------------------------------


Short:    Shows ASC Code & copies it to clipboard
Uploader: Free_Jack@gmx.net
Author:   Free_Jack@gmx.net
Type:     util/wb
Version:  V1.03

ASCII-Clip is a little tool which shows all 256
ISO Latin-1 ASCII Codes and copies the selected one
to the clipboard from which it can be pasted in any
programm which supports the clipboard.

This is useful if you can't remember a specific
ASCII Code or the editor you are using does not allow
most ASCII Codes (like the Blitz Basic Editor)

Written in Blitz Basic 2

Catalog .cd file included
Source (ASCII & bb2) included
german Catalog file included

-----------------------------------snap------------------------------

Because it is so short I have also added to this mail.

I hope you enjoy it !

-- 
-- 
