@NODE "Mail_371" "Re: COme on then all you harden Amiga OS hackers ;)"
 for scott@online.u-net.com; Wed, 7 Apr 1999 14:40:08 +0000
From: "Paul" <paulwest@stationone.demon.co.uk>
Organization: private
Date: 7 Apr 99 14:03:17 +0000
Subject: Re: COme on then all you harden Amiga OS hackers ;)
Encoding: 7bit

Dave,

> AimWidth=640, AimHeight=480, AimDepth=8
> 
> But I can`t seem to figure out how to match that to display modes...I`ve
> looked in dimensioninfo and all I ever seem to get is a max depth of 8, and
> 16384 for width..and some other preset for height. It`s funny how a modeid
> on mine (aga) like 0 has 8 planes..but they do anyway....anyone know which
> bits of info I should be comparing against?? (MonitorInfo??)

Nah just look in the .DimensionInfo, aquired with GetDisplayInfoData
or whatever, and take a look at the TextOScan structure. Pretty much
always a screen is opened with the text overscan settings as standard.
Looking at the MinX and MinY, or even MaxX and MaxY, you can find the
size that that particular display mode will default to. So if you want
a 640x480 mode you should just look through till you find one whose
size will accomodate it. Notably, graphics card modes are set up to
specific sizes (as opposed to the way that AGA lets you have different
dimensions for a given modeID), so will be preset at a particularly
size. e.g. a lores 320x240 mode will be only that size. But anyway,
you basically want to look at the TextOScan, or possibly as someone
else said the nominal thing.


