	charset="iso-8859-1"
Encoding: 7bit

Hi...liked the topic?? ;)

I`m soooo fed up with os stuff ;)...anyway...try and get your teeth round
this

I`ve written a auto screen setup for my fast graphics system (ie, as my
fgfx can use planar or chunky). It detects the optimal screen setting for
you (ie, modeid). Then it could say, load all the chunky gfx in and convert
it to planar if need be, and then simply use the planar versions of chunky
commands. (ie, you would just call FGfx_Box to draw a box, and that would
draw the box, on whatever bitmap format it`s been given). Anyway, I you can
select the screen mode from an asl requester..or use an overide id, if you
don`t want it asking ever time you play the game (ie, load a game prefs file
for a one time screen mode selection). But I want to add autodetection, so
alteast it has the option, and if it gives you a duff res..you can force it
to what you like.

Basically, you step through every single modeid available on the target
computer (this is all 2.0+, that`s why I`m not using crappymodeidA) with
NextDisplayInfo to provide a list of all possible ModeId`s. Then all I need
to do is compare each of those to a my required spec...ie

AimWidth=640, AimHeight=480, AimDepth=8

But I can`t seem to figure out how to match that to display modes...I`ve
looked in dimensioninfo and all I ever seem to get is a max depth of 8, and
16384 for width..and some other preset for height. It`s funny how a modeid
on mine (aga) like 0 has 8 planes..but they do anyway....anyone know which
bits of info I should be comparing against?? (MonitorInfo??)



Dave

P.s. Here`s an extraction from the byteman column in the uk northen computer
markets booklet:

My Man of the month award goes to an Australian called Shane Brooks. This
talented guy has had the audacity to do what Microsoft have said is an
impossibility. He has probably done more to advance the frontiers of modern
technology since the Amiga showed Bill Gates what a Windows environment can
do!

;)...and you wanna know what he did?? Go see http://www.98lite.net ;) (wish
I`d thought of that..could have sold the details to the publishers of
netscape and opera!!!)



