@NODE "Mail_388" "curved lines again"
 for scott@online.u-net.com; Mon, 5 Apr 1999 05:31:27 +0100
From: Petri Keckman <petri.keckman@mbnet.fi>
Date: Fri, 05 Mar 1999 07:29:50 -0500
Subject: curved lines again

--BOUNDARY.7733.2537.2014373768.1


Hello again. The little program is now attached. Should not be difficulties
with characters. It's not very funny, but i think it is guite funny.

Does your eys lies or are the horizontal lines curves? Try and see...



--BOUNDARY.7733.2537.2014373768.1




;Hello again. The little program is now attached.
;Does your eys lies or are the horizontal lines curves? Try and see...

;maxx=640
;maxy=256
;Screen 0,0,0,maxx,maxy,3,$8000,T$,1,0  ;PAL-Hires

maxx=1280
maxy=512
Screen 0,0,0,maxx,maxy,7,$29024,T$,1,0  ;PAL-Super-Hires-Laced
ScreensBitMap 0,0

AGARGB 0,240,240,240
AGARGB 1,240,240,240
AGARGB 2,240,240,240
AGARGB 3,240,240,240
AGARGB 4,0,0,0
AGARGB 5,130,130,130

dx=maxx/17.5
dy=maxy/15
Box 0,0,maxx-1,maxy-1,4

flag.b=False
For y=-dy/2 To maxy-1 Step dy
   Line 1,y,maxx-1,y,5
   For x=-flag*dx/2 To maxx Step 2*dx
      Boxf x+1,y+1,x+dx-1,y+dy-1,4
   Next x
   flag=NOT(flag)
Next y
MouseWait






--BOUNDARY.7733.2537.2014373768.1

