@NODE "Mail_397" "Re: Cybergraphics Problem"
 for scott@online.u-net.com; Sun, 4 Apr 1999 00:13:38 +0100
From: "Paul" <paulwest@stationone.demon.co.uk>
Organization: private
Date: 4 Apr 99 00:12:11 +0000
Subject: Re: Cybergraphics Problem
Encoding: 7bit

> I'm using the routines in mscreen to output the the graphics card.  
> Reserving graphics card mem and using mblockscroll to copy my buffers. 
> I've changed the display ID to the apropriate cybergraphx screenmode.  All
> that is displaying is the cursor. 

Try MScreen2 instead. The old method of doing the output with
blockscroll was not at all reliable especially under cybergraphics. In
MScreen2 the mem pointers are aquired safely and bitmaps locked
properly.

-- 
Paul.

