From: Curt Esser <camge@ix.netcom.com>
Date: Sun, 04 Apr 1999 20:07:34 -0500
Subject: Re: Cybergraphics Problem

--BOUNDARY.1748331416.1

Hi Andrew,

On 04-Apr-99, Andrew Guard wrote:

>> 
> As well you must not forget that VAL commaned is BUGGY.  I found that
> out sometime ago, I found an answer to it and so 2 other people
> have aswell found answers to the VAL bug.
> 
> I think it on Aminet in Blitz January99 *BlitzlstJan99.lha* listing of
> the ml. On the subject titled *Found a bug in VAL commaned*.
> 
> As point of intrest code writen for CGX, Picasso will work on both
> systems with out problem.  I had the same problem as you and it was
> only VAL issue.  Make shore the value it _correct_.

Well, I also had a problem with the VAL command, and GFX card screen ID
numbers.
Here is my replacement for VAL -  I hope it helps.

                                    Yours electronically,
                                    Curt Esser
                                    camge@ix.netcom.com
                                    http://members.xoom.com/Curt_Esser/


--BOUNDARY.1748331416.1
Content-Disposition: attachment; filename="ValFix.asc"

;camge@ix.netcom.com
;last modified Jan 1 1999
;returns correct value for ALL input strings

Function.l  value{input$}
  valu.l=0              ;long for value to be put into
  chars.w=StrToLong_(&input$,&valu)
  Function Return valu
End Function

;-----------------------------------------------------
;====== Example: =====================================

test$="1087504386"       ;Blitz can't do this one right

Bltz$=Hex$(Val(test$))   ;Blitz's answer
Our$=Hex$(value{test$})  ;our function's answer

NPrint "Correct answer is : $40D20002"
NPrint "Blitz's Val() says: $",Bltz$
NPrint "our value{} says  : $",Our$

MouseWait
End





--BOUNDARY.1748331416.1

