On Thu, 1 Apr 1999, Andrew Wheeler wrote:

> Hi,
> 
>     It it possible to execute a shell command from blitz, that stores the
> results in a string
> 
> e.g  if I were to execute c:avail from blitz, I want what it returns to be
> placed in a string 
> 

c:avail >ram:test.output

then you can read it from ram.

