@NODE "Mail_405" "Re: Dirs & Files"
 for scott@online.u-net.com; Sat, 3 Apr 1999 00:03:52 +0000
Date: Sat, 3 Apr 1999 01:10:39 +0100
From: BaH <brucey@thenet.co.uk>
Subject: Re: Dirs & Files

Hi,

It's a sad day when I've sat at my desk on a Friday night and worked on
someone else's problem. (as opposed to my own)........


>Could one of you kind folk, give me or explain to me how I check a directory
>to see if it is empty.
>
>If it isn't empty it returns an error.


Okay, as I had nothing else going on tonight, I came up with this -

; **********
DEFTYPE .FileInfoBlock fib

testdir.s="ram:test"      ; This is a test dir you make there.
                          ; run it when the dir is empty.
                          ; Put something in, and run again.
mylock.l=Lock_(testdir,-2)

If mylock>0
  Examine_ mylock,&fib
  If NOT ExNext_(mylock,&fib)     ; Checks for next file/dir in locked dir.
                                  ; Will return False if nothing there.
    NPrint "Dir is Empty"
  Else
    NPrint "There is something in there"
  EndIf
  UnLock_(mylock)
EndIf
End
; **********

There ya goes.
I used that as a base for a recursive directory search I did somewhere...

Anyone want to rewrite the Autodocs for Blitz as it takes too bloody long
to decipher much of the explanations ????

Have fun

Brucey

