@NODE "Mail_407" "Dodgy system clocks"
 for scott@online.u-net.com; Tue, 20 Apr 1999 14:43:30 +0100
Comments: Authenticated sender is <childm@vax.sbu.ac.uk>
From: "Mike Child" <mike.child@sbu.ac.uk>
Date: Tue, 20 Apr 1999 13:41:36 +0000
Encoding: 7BIT
Subject: Dodgy system clocks


Oliver Mark & James L Boyd & Jamie Bentley all posted messages dated 
January 1978.

I vaguely remember someone cursing their (blizzard) system clock a 
while ago...

Anyway its just occurred to me that someone might have a use for the 
clock module I've got lying around at home (plugs into the floppy 
drive port) - if the blizzard clock didn't override it that is - 
anyway, its no use to me so if anyone wants it let me know...(free)

Mike Child

