Date: Sun, 01 Jan 1978 01:35:01 +0100
Organization: Joker Developments
Subject: FAO: Chris Deeney & David McMinn  (members of blitz-list@netsoc.ucd.ie)

Hi all,
       This message is aimed primarily at Chris Deeney & David McMinn. I
don't have their email addresses, so I just hope they still read mail from
this list.

CHRIS: Do you still have that Wrapping code that u sent me (for use in
NetDOCK-2) 
DAVID: Do u still have that example code for GTSliders. I lost that as well

I just started using PFS2, apparently very stable. Bryan Ollocks! I just had
to format my hard drive, because, if I booted up with DH1: enabled, it
locked up. I had to disalbe dh1: and boot from dh0: naturally, because dh1:
wasn't mounted, I couldn't salvage anything, so I've lost my ND2 source, my
AM*S source, and countless other valuable items.

Thanx in adv, and here's hoping!
Cya!
