@NODE "Mail_428" "Re: Finding executable's name"
 for scott@online.u-net.com; Sun, 18 Apr 1999 14:37:48 +0100
From: James L Boyd <jamesboyd@all-hail.freeserve.co.uk>
Date: Sat, 07 Jan 1978 16:16:32 +0000
Subject: Re: Finding executable's name
Encoding: quoted-printable

Tony Rolfe churned out *this* drivel:

> Can anyone explain how I can get the full name (including path) of the
> current executable program?    I want to extract tooltypes from it's
> Icon.   =


I've pasted two functions below which'll do it (from StatsFuncs, blah bla=
h ;)
 =

One point to note though - /it only works from an executable/, so I'd rec=
ommend
doing something like prog$=3DProgsDir${}+ProgsName${} near the start - th=
is way you
can rename prog$ to the path on your setup while developing, then just co=
mment
it out when you release it...

Your tooltypes stuff would then just be like : a$=3DFindToolValue (prog$)=
, etc...

> Also is RIToolTypes.obj the best way to go?

If you just want to read the tooltypes, I've got code to do that via the =
OS,
otherwise, I'd use RIToolTypes...

Here we go...
 =

Function.s ProgsDir{}

  MaxLen path$=3D200
  NameFromLock_ GetProgramDir_(),&path$,200
  path$=3DPeek$(&path$)
  If Right$(path$,1)<>":" AND Right$(path$,1)<>"/"
    path$+"/"
  EndIf
Function Return path$
End Function

Function.s ProgsName{}

If FromCLI=3D-1

  *stringbuffer =3D AllocMem_(255, 0)
  suc.l=3DGetProgramName_(*stringbuffer,255)

  If suc
    pname$=3DPeek$(*stringbuffer)
  EndIf

  FreeMem_ *stringbuffer,255

Else pname$=3DPeek$(Peek.l(FindTask_(0)+$B0)+4)
EndIf

If pname$=3D"" Then pname$=3D"Run from Blitz!"

Function Return pname$

End Function

; demo :

a$=3DProgsDir{}+ProgsName{}
Request "","Program : "+a$,"Try moving/renaming it now!"
End

See ya,
-- =

<tsb>
<sb>James L Boyd - jamesboyd@all-hail.freeserve.co.uk
<sb>Member of Team *AMIGA*, and *Dogbert's New Ruling Class.*
<sb>Connected from Dundee, Scotland. =

