easy stuff) but not writing. Can't remember who wrote it though ;)

> Speaking of which, does anyone know how to read a string array
> from within an OS structure into a Blitz array?
> 
> eg .DiskObject\do_ToolTypes ( char ** array ) ...?

I've recently found out that you can do really cool things with newtypes w=
ith 
arrays, which are well suited to this.

Check out the attached source.


|) /\ \/ ][ |)   |\/| =A9 |\/| ][ |\| |\|
 dmcminn@house-of-mojo.freeserve.co.uk
  http://members.xoom.com/David_McMinn
             ICQ=3D16827694
'There can be only one' - MacLeod



--Message-Boundary-5203
encoding: 7BIT
Content-description: Text from file 'arraynewtype.asc'

NEWTYPE.badhack1
  array.l[0]
End NEWTYPE

*do.DiskObject=GetDiskObject_("work:scrollingtricks/readme")
If *do
  *tt.badhack1 = *do\do_ToolTypes
  i.w=0
  While(*tt\array[i]<>0)
    NPrint Peek.s(*tt\array[i])
    i+1
  Wend
  FreeDiskObject_ *do
End If

Stop
End



--Message-Boundary-5203

