For additional commands, e-mail: blitz-list-help@netsoc.ucd.ie



@ENDNODE
@NODE "Mail_440" "Re: Flunking Maths"
 for scott@online.u-net.com; Mon, 5 Apr 1999 11:50:28 +0000
From: "David McMinn" <D.Mcminn@eee.rgu.ac.uk>
Organization: The Robert Gordon University, E&EE
Date: Mon, 5 Apr 1999 12:50:09 +0100
encoding: Quoted-printable
Subject: Re: Flunking Maths

> So, can anybody tell me where the problem is?

 Bug in the VAL command when using numbers which can only fit into longs. =
A few 
people on this list have workarounds.

However, if it is only for storing a display ID, why not use:

    Print Mkl$(display ID)
 when writing to the file and:

    displayID.l=3DCvl(Inkey$(4)) 
 when reading from it. The display ID won't be stored as ASCII, but who ca=
res, 
its not something the user should be messing with. And if they are power u=
sers, 
they'll likely have a hex editor anyway.
|) /\ \/ ][ |)   |\/| =A9 |\/| ][ |\| |\|
