@NODE "Mail_444" "Re: Fonts"
 for scott@online.u-net.com; Sun, 18 Apr 1999 17:50:38 +0000
From: "David McMinn" <D.Mcminn@eee.rgu.ac.uk>
Organization: The Robert Gordon University, E&EE
Date: Sun, 18 Apr 1999 17:47:47 +0100
encoding: Quoted-printable
Subject: Re: Fonts



> Could someone tell me why my program keeps on using topaz8 even while I
> force load topaz11 or sth else. Also even if I do not load any font and
> any other font i use on wb(icon, system, screen fonts) are non topaz8. I
> load fonts with NCS commands.
> 
> Seems no way for me to get the gadgets to use anything BUT topaz8. I don=
t
> care, but there r people who prefer font sensitivity et all.

 If you are using NCS for everything, then you probably need to specify th=
e 
font when you are creating the gadgets, not just loading the font


; You need amigalibs.res

DEFTYPE.TextAttr fonttouse

; Uses topaz11
fname$=3D"fonts:topaz.font"
fonttouse\&fname$,11,#FS_NORMAL,#FPF_DISKFONT

NSetGadgetFont &fonttouse

; create your NCS gadgets here


|) /\ \/ ][ |)   |\/| =A9 |\/| ][ |\| |\|
 dmcminn@house-of-mojo.freeserve.co.uk
