@NODE "Mail_445" "For those who want free local calls! :)"
 for scott@online.u-net.com; Wed, 21 Apr 1999 13:21:59 +0100
From: "Matt Briggs" <s9225796@rothervalley.ac.uk>
	<blitz-list@netsoc.ucd.ie>
Subject: For those who want free local calls! :)
Date: Wed, 21 Apr 1999 13:18:29 +0100
	charset="iso-8859-1"
Encoding: 7bit


CUT and Sunday 6th June 1999


Some of you may have seen this message (or one like it) in one of the many
other places we announce things, and some of you may get this more than
once. Our apologies in advance if you have.

First of all, a belated thank you to many of you for signing 'I agree with
the aims of CUT'. Belated because we don't want to bombard people with
email: this one is important, though, and is going out to a great many
people. 

On Sunday 6 June we are taking part in a European Telecommunications
Boycott with nine other European countries. The formal announcement is at: 

http://www.unmetered.org.uk/news/news210499.htm 

The aim is for as many people as possible in those countries to pull out
their telephone plugs, and lay down their modems, for 24 hours on that day
in protest at high telecommunications charging in most EU countries, not
just ours. 

We're encouraging all telephone users, not just Internet users, to take
part. So, without the telephone bell or the computer to annoy you, you can
spend that Sunday doing all these things you've been putting off. I'll be
reading a couple of books which have lain unopened for months because of
CUT taking up so much time. 

You can do several things to help: 

1. Take part and tell all your friends, relatives and Internet contacts
what's going on. 

2. Forward the CUT press release to all the organisations you know of:
http://www.unmetered.org.uk/press/pr_210499.txt 

The Press Pack (http://www.unmetered.org.uk/press/) has background
information which will let the media know what we're about, plus our
contact details, so don't worry about having to summarise what we do
yourself. 

3. Put a link to the announcement of the event on your Web site - if you
have one - or, even better, get your company to put the link up in its Web
site. You can find the graphic and HTML you need to make the link at: 

http://www.unmetered.org.uk/graphics/vivi.zip 

4. Add the two lines following to your email and news signature: 

6 June 1999 - European Telecommunications Boycott 
In the UK: http://www.unmetered.org.uk/ 

5. If you've not done so already, consider becoming a full member of CUT;
have a look at the site again and, if you like what you see, please sign
up. We now take credit card memberships via a secure server. 	

6. And when 6th June comes along, take down your own web site altogether
and replace it with only the link to the campaign. Of course, don't forget
to put it back up again at the end of the Boycott! If you don't have a web
site yet, make one especially for the occasion! Your own ISP probably gives
you space as part of your service, and if not, there are plenty of "free"
web prividers around. 

There will be lots of things happening between now and then, so please
visit the site from time to time for updates and further news.

6th June is the anniversary of D-Day. This is *our* D-Day, when we tell the
telcos, the regulators, and all the other cosy partners in the Great Phone
Waltz that enough is enough! We're fighting back and won't give ground any
more!


-- 
Richard Sliwa
Campaign for Unmetered Telecommunications
Support the European Telecommunications Boycott on 6 June:
http://www.unmetered.org.uk 






