@NODE "Mail_450" "Re: Gadget Trouble"
 for scott@online.u-net.com; Fri, 2 Apr 1999 22:43:40 +0000
From: Curt Esser <camge@ix.netcom.com>
Date: Fri, 02 Apr 1999 16:20:27 -0500
Subject: Re: Gadget Trouble

--BOUNDARY.1748524440.1

Hi Jake

On 01-Apr-99, Jake Frederick wrote:
>    Is it that no one could answer my question about gadgets or did you
> just not see it because my clock was messed up? In case it was the latter,
> here it is again:

Yeah, the clock it was!  In fact, I just found it down at the bottom of the
pile of "emails I'll get around to in a day or so"  ;)
> 
>    Does someone have an example of a functional slider using GTTags? I
> can set
> the level using GTSetAttrs and #GTSL_level but for some reason I can't set
> the max level length using #GTSL_MaxLevelLen.

Here is a slider example I snipped out of a program - I hope it helps.

> Also how can I read the
> active option on a cycle gadget?

Eventcode will tell you which "face" is currently showing on your cycle gad
after the cycle gadget is "hit"

                                    Yours electronically,
                                    Curt Esser
                                    camge@ix.netcom.com
                                    http://members.xoom.com/Curt_Esser/


--BOUNDARY.1748524440.1
Content-Disposition: attachment; filename="slider.asc"

WBenchToFront_
WbToScreen 0

; -- Gadget ID numbers: --

#widthview = 50
#heightview =51
#yes =52
#no = 53
#xpsize = 54

; -- Just some stuff patched in to replace the whole rest of the program -
;    don't worry about 'em

xpx.w=320
xpy.w=200
win_width=320
Xmax=900
winscale=xpy/xpx


; -- The GTGadgetList

GTTags #GTTX_Justification,#GTJ_CENTER,#GTNM_Clipped,True
GTText   4,#widthview,66,46,65,23,"Width",#PLACETEXT_BELOW,Str$(xpx)

GTTags #GTTX_Justification,#GTJ_CENTER,#GTNM_Clipped,True
GTText   4,#heightview,226,46,65,23,"Height",#PLACETEXT_BELOW,Str$(xpy)

GTButton 4,#yes,26,118,126,16,"OK",$80|#PLACETEXT_IN

GTButton 4,#no,204,118,126,16,"Cancel",$80|#PLACETEXT_IN

GTSlider 4,#xpsize,26,89,304,16,"",$80|8,win_width,Xmax
GTSetAttrs 4,#xpsize,#GTSL_Level,xpx

AddIDCMP $20|$10   ;-- for immediate output from the slider ----

; -- finally, a window opens! --

Window 4,138,130,364,158,$1000,"Buffer Export",1,2
offx.b = WLeftOff
AttachGTList 4,4
WLocate 50,26
Print"Set the size for the iff picture:"

gd=0

Repeat
  ev.l=WaitEvent
    If ev=$20          ;a gadget was hit
      gd=GadgetHit

      If gd=#xpsize    ;read the slider
        Repeat         ;and keep updating
          ev.l=Event   ;as long as it is held down
          xpx=EventCode
          xpy=xpx*winscale
          VWait
          GTSetAttrs 4,#widthview,#GTTX_Text,Str$(xpx)
          VWait
          GTSetAttrs 4,#heightview,#GTTX_Text,Str$(xpy)
        Until ev=$40
      EndIf

    EndIf

Until gd=#yes OR gd=#no


End


--BOUNDARY.1748524440.1

