@NODE "Mail_451" "Re: Gadget Trouble (again!)"
 for scott@online.u-net.com; Sat, 3 Apr 1999 20:48:42 +0000
From: Jean-Marc GIGANDET <HURRICAN@wanadoo.fr>
Date: Sat, 03 Apr 1999 21:36:39 +0200
Subject: Re: Gadget Trouble (again!)
Encoding: quoted-printable

Hello Jake

First, remember this : don't use gadget numbers lower than 50 (Gadtools b=
ug).
Then try something like this for your cycle gadgets :

      Result.l =3D GTGetAttrs(#NumGadgetList,#NumGadget,#GTCY_Active)

#GTCY_Active is a constant figuring in Amigalibs.res.

Regards
-- =

HURRICAN@wanadoo.fr
A1200 030/28 + 68881 + 8 Mo + Quantum 635 Mo + Wd 60 Mo + M1438S + Deskje=
t 690C + UsR 33600.
HURRICANE, TURRICAN, well, that's a good mix. Both should visit Redmond .=
