@NODE "Mail_455" "Re: Gfx cards....how deep do they go??"
 for scott@online.u-net.com; Thu, 15 Apr 1999 20:19:41 +0100
Date: Thu, 15 Apr 1999 20:20:50 +0100
From: Paul Burkey <burkey@bigfoot.com>
X-Accept-Language: en
Subject: Re: Gfx cards....how deep do they go??
Encoding: 7bit

Dave wrote:
>  Just a quick simple question.....how many bits can be used on the current
> range of amiga gfx cards?? I`m looking at 24 bit YUV (well Y'CbCr for video
> experts...as I`m sure I`ll get flame if I say YUV).....Well, more like
> Y'CbCr 4:2:0, which`ll give me 8 bit Y', and CbCr will be 8bit each with an
> accruacy of 2*2.
>  Enough of the tech stuff....basically, I can output to any rgb format...I
> figure I can cheat and use a fixed palette on 8 bit paletted (aga
> etc)....with RRRGGGBB (those are bits...making 0-255)..and then on other bit
> depths I can simply convert to RGB formats (0RRRRRGGGGGBBBBB for 16 bit for
> example)......and I was just wondering how many people will be able to
> display 16 and 24 bit displays.....

All Amiga gfx cards seem to support 15bit 16bit and 24bit and possibly
some of the newer amiga cards have 32bit modes which are common on PC
gfx cards. You should presume that any card can have any pixel format.
The exact format of the pixels will depend on the card itself. You
should
read the cybergraphx developer info for details on the various pixel
formats supported such as:-

PIXFMT_LUT8
PIXFMT_RGB15
PIXFMT_BGR15
PIXFMT_RGB15PC
PIXFMT_BGR15PC
PIXFMT_RGB16
PIXFMT_BGR16
PIXFMT_RGB16PC
PIXFMT_BGR16PC
PIXFMT_RGB24
PIXFMT_BGR24
PIXFMT_ARGB32
PIXFMT_BGRA32
PIXFMT_RGBA32

Cheers,

Paul


-- 
< Paul Burkey http://www.sneech.freeserve.co.uk >

