From: "Evan Tuer" <et@enterprise.net>
Organization: !
Date: 15 Apr 99 21:02:44 +0100
Subject: Re: Gfx cards....how deep do they go??
Encoding: 7bit

On Thu, 15 Apr 1999 17:45:57 +0100, Dave wrote:
> Hi all,

>  Enough of the tech stuff....basically, I can output to any rgb format...I
> figure I can cheat and use a fixed palette on 8 bit paletted (aga
> etc)....with RRRGGGBB (those are bits...making 0-255)..and then on other bit
> depths I can simply convert to RGB formats (0RRRRRGGGGGBBBBB for 16 bit for
> example)......and I was just wondering how many people will be able to
> display 16 and 24 bit displays.....

16 bit would catch everyone.  Most gfx cards can do 24 bit, but often
only at 800x600 or less.  Mine even does 32 bit, but I think only at
640x480 or something like that.

Personally I still use an 8 bit screen for workbench :)  Mainly
because everything ever written to work on workbench can only use 8
bits.  For anything needing more colours (V, ImageX) I open more
screens anyway, otherwise it'll get too crowded.

