@NODE "Mail_472" "Re: GTButtons"
 for scott@online.u-net.com; Mon, 19 Apr 1999 08:29:21 +0100
From: Curt Esser <camge@ix.netcom.com>
Date: Fri, 19 Apr 1991 02:21:27 -0500
Subject: Re: GTButtons

--BOUNDARY.1748506776.1

Hi Tony

On 18-Apr-99, Tony Rolfe wrote:
> 
> Is it possible to change the text in a GTButton "on the fly"?
> 
> If so, how?

Here's the only way I know:

Detach the GTlist
remake it with the new text(s)
Re-attach it to the window.

Example attached.

                                    Yours electronically,
                                    Curt Esser
                                    camge@ix.netcom.com
                                    http://members.xoom.com/Curt_Esser/


--BOUNDARY.1748506776.1
Content-Disposition: attachment; filename="BtnChange.asc"


;first, let's grab the WB screen

NoCli          ;it would just be in the way...
WBenchToFront_
FindScreen 0



Window 0,160,20,320,150,$1000|$8,"Button Change",1,0

NPrint " "
NPrint "   Click the buttons to change"

;now let's create a gadgetlist:

Dim btntxt$(3)

btntxt$(1)="Click me!"
btntxt$(2)="No, click me!"
btntxt$(3)="Please, click me!"

Gosub makeGTlist

AttachGTList 0,0

Repeat
  ev.l=WaitEvent
  If ev=$40
    Select GadgetHit
      Case 1
        btntxt$(1)="Thanks!"
        btntxt$(2)="Why not me?"
        btntxt$(3)="Oh, PLEASE!"
      Case 2
        btntxt$(1)="Hey!"
        btntxt$(2)="Aaaahhh!"
        btntxt$(3)="I'm waiting!"
      Case 3
        btntxt$(1)="Come on!"
        btntxt$(2)="It's MY turn!"
        btntxt$(3)="I needed that!"
    End Select
    DetachGTList 0
    Free GTList 0
    Gosub makeGTlist
    AttachGTList 0,0
  EndIf
Until ev=$200

End


makeGTlist

GTButton 0,1,70,35,165,26,btntxt$(1),0
GTButton 0,2,70,65,165,26,btntxt$(2),0
GTButton 0,3,70,95,165,26,btntxt$(3),0

Return


--BOUNDARY.1748506776.1

