Cute Example, Curt.

I was really trying to emulate the MUI thing where you click on a
button to get a list of choices and put the chosen one in the button
(a cycle to menu type thing).   If I have to redraw the whole GTList I
have to store  all other input in the window to recreate earlier
input.

I'm currently doing it by printing into the button, (the button
text is a "prompt" to the left and the button contents are printed in
there).   I had hoped there was a more elegant way.

Did like the code though!


