On 28 Apr 99 08:45:04 +0100 Simon Hitchen said:
> Hello John,
>  
> > Intuition, becase some string gadgets allow you to tab out of them to a
> > new one.  This is probably being done by the program, not the OS since it
> > doesn't always work..  I could of course be wrong though... :)
> 
> Now you mention it, I wrote a little proggy a while ago that had six
> string gadgets in it's window. You could press TAB to cycle the cursor
> from one to the next and the program had no routines to do this.
> 
> A feature of Intuition ?.
Yes.   Tab and Shift-tab (by default) tab to the next string-type
gadget.  You can set this off by using the #GFLG_TABCYCLE flag when
tab and shift-tab do NOTHING (no gadgetup or down IDCMP messages).
Return and Enter always give a gadgetup message but do not
automatically activate the next gadget.

If anyone knows how to deactivate a gadget I'll be eternally grateful
(at least I will be if you actually tell me how).

Cheers

