Hi David

On 30-Apr-99, David McMinn wrote:
>> Yeah, I wrote a program that tabbed as well, but my program checked for
>> the IDCMP to find out which string gadget the user had tabbed from, and
>> then activated the most appropriate string gadget afterwards.
> 
> How do you do that then? I couldn't find a way to deactivate the string
> gadget that Intuition had activated after pressing tab.

Here is a string tabbing example that shows how to set up your gadgetlist so
you can have it tab where you want, and also skip a gadget unless it is
clicked into.

Handy if you have something like:

Name:
Address:
Country:
Telephone:

But want to use the default Country entry unless you click into it.


Oh, and if for some reason you simply want to de-activate ALL the string
gadgets in the window, try this:

DetachGTlist (whatever)
AttachGTlist (whatever,whatever)

Later...
-- 
Might as well be frank, Monsieur. 
It would take a miracle to get you out of Casablanca.

                                    Yours electronically,
                                    Curt Esser
                                    camge@ix.netcom.com
                                    http://members.xoom.com/Curt_Esser/


--BOUNDARY.1748500560.1
Content-Disposition: attachment; filename="TabExamp.asc"

;GT string tabbing
;notice that the tabbing is done according to the order
;of the gadget creation - it has nothing to do with the
;gadget id# or the physical location of the gadgets
;in the window - that's why I made the gadgets out
;of order

WBenchToFront_
FindScreen 0

GTString 0,51, 10,  10,200,20,"first here",$8|$80,30,"Way"
GTString 0,52, 240, 50,200,20,"second",$8|$80,30,"the"
GTString 0,53, 10,  90,200,20,"no-tab",$8|$80,30,"Swanee"
GTString 0,55, 240, 10,200,20,"third",$8|$80,30,"down"
GTString 0,56, 10,  50,200,20,"fourth",$8|$80,30,"upon"
GTString 0,54, 240, 90,200,20,"fifth",$8|$80,30,"River"

Window 0,20,20,480,180,$1000|$8," GTString Tabbing",1,0
AttachGTList 0,0
ActivateString 0,51

Repeat
  ev.l=WaitEvent
  Select ev

    Case $20                         ;gadget down
      If GadgetHit=53 AND Joyb(0)=0  ;skip this one if tabbed into
        DetachGTList 0               ;but use it if clicked into
        AttachGTList 0,0
        ActivateString 0,55
      EndIf
      lastgad=currgad

    Case $200                        ;window close
      End

  End Select
Forever



--BOUNDARY.1748500560.1

