@NODE "Mail_500" "GTString Gadgets"
 for scott@online.u-net.com; Sun, 18 Apr 1999 08:41:47 +0100
From: "Tony Rolfe" <edgewater@shoalhaven.net.au>
Organization: Edgewater Motel, Burrill Lake, NSW 2539 Australia
Date: 18 Apr 99 17:33:21 +1000
Subject: GTString Gadgets
Encoding: 7bit

Some time ago I asked if anyone knew how to find the currently active
gadget.    David pointed me in the right direction and I've come up
with the following code.    It is supposed to activate a different
string from the currently active one.

Can anyone tell me why it doesn't work?

It seems to deactivate the active string, but still does not activate
the new one.   At least, the cursor disappears, but if you hit return
or tab after this code, the previously active string is invoked - so I
guess it isn't really deactivated.

Any ideas anyone?

Statement Activate_String{Gadget.w}

*WIN.Window = Peek.l(Addr Window (Used Window))
*GAD.Gadget = *WIN\FirstGadget
While *GAD
   If *GAD\Flags & #GFLG_SELECTED
      If *GAD\GadgetID <> Gadget
         *GAD\Flags - #GFLG_SELECTED
         Redraw Used Window, *GAD\GadgetID
      EndIf
      *GAD = 0
   Else
      *GAD = *GAD\NextGadget
   EndIf
Wend

ActivateString Used Window, Gadget     ; Activate the string
Redraw Used Window, Gadget

End Statement

Yours hopefully

-- 
Tony Rolfe
Amiga 2000, 68030/25, 1+4Mb
www.shoalhaven.net.au/edgewater

