> Can anyone tell me why it doesn't work?

OK, for a start, you can only look at and initialise the #GFLG_SELECTED fl=
ag, 
intuition will keep track of it, that is why your string gadget get re-
activated.

You may want to try changing the disabled flag, like in the code I sent yo=
u, 
but not redrawing the gadgets, I can't remember any of the code.

 And when you are dealing with flags, you do not use + and -, you need to =
use & 
(and) and | (or), as bit flags are separate, logical bits.


