Subject: Re: GTString Gadgets
Encoding: quoted-printable

    Hi Tony, =


> BTW, are AND and & interchangeable?   I've never really understood the
> difference.

    It does the same but the priority of the operand aren't the same ! So=

& and | are high priority (higher than * and /) and AND OR NOT are low
priority (lower than + -).
    =

    ie: (a&o+2) will not give the same result than (a AND o+2)

        I hope this help,

-- =


                        Fred.

