@NODE "Mail_511" "Help needed!"
 for scott@online.u-net.com; Thu, 8 Apr 1999 20:30:19 +0100
From: Pekka Nissinen <pekka.nissinen@pp2.inet.fi>
Date: Thu, 08 Apr 1999 08:27:04 +0200
Subject: Help needed!
Resent-From: S Beardwood <scott@online.u-net.com>
Resent-Date: Thu, 08 Apr 1999 20:29:45 +0000
Resent-Message-Id: <E10VKUj-0003Gv-00@mserv1b.u-net.net>
Resent-Bcc:

Hi!

I recently started to write a GUI to one of my old BlizBasic programs.
I tought that a GUI using MUI was the best solution, so I downloaded the
EFMUILibrary archive from Aminet. First everything was progressing fine, but
then I fell into problem that interrupted my work.

Of course the reason why I'm having this problem, might be the fact that my
experience in programming is WERY low! 
But anyway, if anyone could help me with this problem, I'd be wery grateful!

The Problem:....

OK! Lets assume that I have a String gadget (for ex. MUIString 1,"",32), that
I use to input/Output numeric values. Since there isn't any specific Integer
Gadget in MUI... (I may be wrong, but I didn't find anything about it in
EFMUILIB.quide or in MUI Developer autodocs...) ...I used the String gadget. I
tried to make it act like a Integer gadget using line: MUISet
1,#MUIA_String_Accept,"0123456789." but it behaved wery strage, so I removed
the line. But that isn't really THE problem...
The REAL trouble is, that how can I read the contents of the gadget? 
Since I can't read numeric values using: a=MUIGetString$(1) or print them
with: MUISetString 1,a 
(I only get that: Can't convert types, blablabla with those lines), I
managed to read it with this line: a=MUIGet(1,#MUIA_String_Integer) and
printing with: MUISet 1,#MUIA_String_Integer,a

But this didn't cure my problem, it only made a new one. 
This reading/printing "method" CAN'T read/print decimals from/to string
gadget! 
For ex. If I have typed number 326.45 to the string gadget, it only returns
the value 326!! Or from a value 0.1234 I only get 0!! Because of the nature of
this program, it's important to be able to read and print values WITH
decimals!

So, if there is a way to do this so, that the decimals aren't ignored, that
would
certainly help things a lot! I could then finish up the GUI...or at least try
to! :)

PS. I almost forget, is there a way to use the Slider gadged with decimals? It
isn't accurate enough to my proggy without them.... 
(I apologize to my poor english..)

My System is:   A1200T + BVision / BlizzardPPC603_240Mhz/68040_25Mhz + 64Mb
FastRAM + 6.4Gb HD + 6x IDE CDRom                                             
                       

Sincerally yours: Pekka Nissinen







