@NODE "Mail_518" "Re: Help Please, remap and gtshape"
 for scott@online.u-net.com; Wed, 21 Apr 1999 10:34:54 +0000
From: "David McMinn" <D.Mcminn@eee.rgu.ac.uk>
Organization: The Robert Gordon University, E&EE
Date: Wed, 21 Apr 1999 10:32:09 +0100
encoding: Quoted-printable
Subject: Re: Help Please, remap and gtshape

> OK, does the above code mean that you can get the gadget address and
> poke values straight into the gadget flags after the GTString and
> before the AttachGTList??     Seems that will solve one of my
> problems.    Thanks David.

I think so. As long as the GTShape actually creates the gadget when you ca=
ll it 
(which it should).

And its not poking values, its carefully setting the flags ;)


