@NODE "Mail_522" "HEX Save"
 for scott@online.u-net.com; Fri, 9 Apr 1999 09:42:01 +0100
From: Gareth Griffiths <gaz@jokerd.idps.co.uk>
Date: Fri, 09 Apr 1999 00:13:48 +0100
Organization: Joker Developments
Subject: HEX Save

Hi,
  I recently discovered the location of the cash data for a Sensible WOrld
Of Soccer 95/96 Career file, and prompty edited it to max :)

I then decided to write a money cheater using Blitz. Howver, when I open the
file for reading, using OpenFile, and then position the pointer in the
write place using FileSeek, if I then write the Hex$(cash) data to the
file, instead of coming up in the HEX part of the file, it comes up in the
ASC part. Is there a way to fix this, to tell blitz to NOT write out
00007840 in ASCII codes, but in HEX, so that it actually works. The way it
does it at the moment, it prints 30784 instead of 00007840.

If I get a good answer, I may continue and do a Cannon Fodder save game
editor, which I recently discovered the file format to. 4-star gneerals for
every soldier, 999 recoreded kills, 2343 enemy soldiers killed. Excellent.
   
Cya!
