>> ASC part. Is there a way to fix this, to tell blitz to NOT write out
>> 00007840 in ASCII codes, but in HEX, so that it actually works. The way
>> it does it at the moment, it prints 30784 instead of 00007840.
> 
> If the data is a long, then use Print Mkl$(var). For words, I think you
> use Mki$.
>
And for a byte, you can use:

byte.b=49
Print CHR$(byte)

Another way:

long.l=650723
word.w=398
byte.b=49

WriteMem 0,&long,4
WriteMem 0,&word,2
WriteMem 0,&byte,1
 

