From: BaH <brucey@thenet.co.uk>
Subject: Re: Hiding the mouse redux

>> Hello,
>>
>> There was a thread a short time ago about hiding the mouse cursor.  What was
>> the end result of that.  Is there a way to remove the cursor from a Mildred
>> display?
>
>There's no such thing as a Mildred display. It's just a normal screen
>so the same method applies to remove the mouse - make a blank sprite
>and use WPointer.


Hokay.  It's all my fault for bringing up the subject.

I had a think on both the ideas for hiding the pointer, but both appear to
require a window (whether it's there or hidden away somewhere).  Maybe I'm
wrong, but if something is looking for a pointer TO a window, you need a
window?

However, I had gone through the Aminet archives in the search of some
source code to help me along, but nothing that I thought did it simply
enough.  Sure, there IS source available for making the pointer vanish in
various ways, but it all looked a bit too cludgy.

I then happened across a couple of small (108 bytes) programs lying around
in a rarely used directory - mouseon & mouseoff.
I tried them out, and hey, they worked !
So, I then IncBin'd them into my program, stuck a call to their relevant
addresses, and there you had it.... a disappearing/reappearing mousepointer
on demand.

It may not be the BEST way to do it, but at 216 bytes, I'm not complaining.

Brucey

