Hi all, 

Right, I'm working on a major hack :)

I've wanted to do this for ages, but someone mentioned poking a window
pointer into a Blitz window object, and that set me off...

I've attached my piss-poor attempt at trying to find when the Workbench
menu item "Quit" is hit, because I think it's about time that item had a
use (ie put up a Reboot? requester).

Can any of you OS experts tell me if I'm on the right track (ignoring
Enforcer hits and everything else nasty about this ;)  ?

Or at least tell me why I could never hope to get this to work in
a million years?

Or beat me to it?

Thanks :)
-- 
<tsb>
<sb>James L Boyd - jamesboyd@all-hail.freeserve.co.uk
<sb>Member of Team *AMIGA*, and *Dogbert's New Ruling Class.*
<sb>Connected from Dundee, Scotland. 
<sb>(http://surf.to/all-hail/)
<tsb>

Institutionalised cruelty is one thing,but the /twisted brain-wrong/
of a one-off man-mental is quite another.
-- Chris Morris, /Brass Eye/

--BOUNDARY.1748065104.2
Content-Disposition: attachment; filename="HackWBMenus.asc"
Content-Description: Help me find the Quit item!

; *** W A R N I N G ! ***
;
; Don't run this unless you know what you're doing!
; VERY dangerous indeed!

; Heh heh :)

; End ; for syntax testing...who needs a "Test" mode? ;)

Function.l WBWinAddr {} ; returns address of WB window

  wb$="Workbench"
  *scr.Screen=LockPubScreen_(&wb$)
  If *scr
    *win.Window = *scr\FirstWindow
    While *win
      If *win\Flags & #WFLG_WBENCHWINDOW
      wb.b=-1
      Goto poppit
      EndIf
      *win = *win\NextWindow
    Wend
  Function Return 0 ; didn't get it!

  poppit
  Function Return *win

  Else Function Return 0
  EndIf

End Function

Poke.l Addr Window (0),WBWinAddr {}  ; make Blitz Window 0 the WB window!

*win.Window=Peek.l (Addr Window (0)) ; right, get a pointer

*MStrip.Menu=*win\MenuStrip          ; probably not correct ;)

Poke.l Addr MenuList (0),*MStrip     ; same again...

