On 16-Apr-99, Rob Hutchinson wrote:
 
> Strange Beast Errors
> ------------------------------------------------
> Optimizer Error! - $': This should never happen. Please report.
> Expression too Complex: Should never happen. Contact mark directly.
> Not Supported: Should never happen.
> Illegal Token: Should never happen.

  Ahh, these are the mystic Blitz error codes- we all live in hope of
one day achieving programming Nirvana, by producing one of them ;-))

> Just wondering, anyone ever got one? And `Optimizer Error' - What
> f`kin optimizer? I haven`t seen one yet ;)

  They had an optimiser in earlier versions- but it was rather buggy, so
it was removed. The option is still there, `cause they were going to
try and put a better one in.
 
> Oh yeah, BTW - Does `Make Smallest code' actually do anything what so
> ever?
 
 Only when run from the Blitz editor, in all the recent versions of
Blitz, it is automatically on for executables. It takes longer to
compile if on.

