> =

> I've had all the last three, but I can't remember how I got them. It wa=
s a
> while ago and I found ways around them. Murphy's law #21 - never say
> things should never happen, as they will always be the first thing to
> happen.

I've just had "Expression To Complex" the other day, I think this is
correct,

--

Newtype.one
    id.w
    name.s
End Newtype

Newtype.two
    address.s
End Newtype

dim hello.one(50)
dim goodbye.two(50)

hello(1)\id=3D1
hello(1)\name=3D"Daniel"

goodbye(1)\address=3D"slash@thesnakepit.demon.co.uk"

USEPATH hello(1)
    print \id
    print \name

USEPATH goodbye(\id)        ; < -- Gives "Expression To Complex" error!!
    print \address

    =


-- =

Cheers,
    Daniel

