@NODE "Mail_581" "Interupts"
 for scott@online.u-net.com; Tue, 13 Apr 1999 13:58:42 +0000
From: Gareth Griffiths <gaz@jokerd.freeserve.co.uk>
Date: Tue, 13 Apr 1999 13:40:02 +0100
Organization: Joker Developments
Subject: Interupts

Hi,
  I'm writing a module player (PT/NT and MMD0/1 atm, anyone know player code
for other formats?) and as it says in the manual (pah!) you should use
Interrupt 5 for playing Meds. So I have, this is the code I use:

#Repeat#
  ev.l=#WaitEvent#
  #SetInt# 5
    #PlayMed#
#  End SetInt#
  #If# ev.l=$200
    #End#
  #EndIf#
  #if# ev.l=$40
    [ event handling routines snipped ]
  #EndIf#
#Until# ev.l=$200
#End#

And when I go to Compile/Run from the menu, it says 'Repeat without Until'.
If I take out the SetInt code, it all works perfectly. It also does it with
If..EndIf statements, For..Next loops etc.

Does anyone else experience this problem, or is it just my SetInt??   
Also, is there any other way of playing meds, without using interrupts or
the VWait thing? A library maybe?

Cya!
-- 
