@NODE "Mail_583" "Re: Interupts"
 for scott@online.u-net.com; Tue, 13 Apr 1999 19:54:46 +0100
From: Rick Hodger <rick.thehub@bigfoot.com>
Date: Tue, 13 Apr 1999 19:15:33 +0100
Organization: Pagan Software
Subject: Re: Interupts

I watched as Gareth Griffiths hammered "Interupts" out on their keyboard...

> Hi,
>  I'm writing a module player (PT/NT and MMD0/1 atm, anyone know player
> code for other formats?) and as it says in the manual (pah!) you should
> use Interrupt 5 for playing Meds. So I have, this is the code I use:

> #Repeat#
>  ev.l=#WaitEvent#
>  #SetInt# 5
>    #PlayMed#
> #  End SetInt#
>  #If# ev.l=$200
>    #End#
>  #EndIf#
>  #if# ev.l=$40
>    [ event handling routines snipped ]
>  #EndIf#
> #Until# ev.l=$200
> #End#

> And when I go to Compile/Run from the menu, it says 'Repeat without
> Until'. If I take out the SetInt code, it all works perfectly. It also
> does it with If..EndIf statements, For..Next loops etc.

> Does anyone else experience this problem, or is it just my SetInt??   
> Also, is there any other way of playing meds, without using interrupts or
> the VWait thing? A library maybe?

You've put the SetInt section inside a Repeat-Until loop.  Don't do that. 
The whole point of an interrupt is that you define it at the start of your
code, and then everytime that interrupt occurs, it will stop what it's
doing and go execute the code held inside the SetInt section.

Anyways, you don't wanna do it that way.  Look up MEDFuncs on aminet, if
they're not there I'll mail 'em to you.  They'll do everything you want,
plus the 8 channel and 64 channel MED's, and they're easier too ;)

-- 
