From: Donovan Reeve <bubby.lnk@ispi.net>
Date: Sat, 10 Apr 1999 17:24:44 +0500
Subject: Keyboards

On 10-Apr-99, Bippy M flashed:
>hiya's,

>I'm looking for a 2nd hand A1200 (Preferably 3.1 Roms), All I want is the
>1200, i don't want the PSU, RF Leads, Mouse or Any software,just a WORKING
>Amiga 1200 OR a working 1200 Keyboard.


  Paxtron Corp. sells the replacement A1200 keyboards for $34.95 U.S.
which is about 25 UK pounds currently.  Don't know if they have UK
keyboards but the difference isn't to bothersome (I know because I am
using a UK keyboard purchased from Software Hut on my A-4000)
  Software Hut no longer lists A-1200 keyboards or I would recomend trying
them as they apparently have UK keyboards.  Paxtron has advertised that
they carry the USA keyboard, but maybe they have the UK one as well.


  PS, sorry for the screwed up reply before...


Donovan Reeve (bubby.lnk@ispi.net)



