@NODE "Mail_599" "Layers..."
 for scott@online.u-net.com; Sun, 4 Apr 1999 22:43:45 +0000
From: James L Boyd <jamesboyd@all-hail.freeserve.co.uk>
Date: Sun, 04 Apr 1999 23:45:04 +0000
Subject: Layers...

--BOUNDARY.1747960104.2

Hi, 

Can anyone tell me why this doesn't work?

I know that I'm not supposed to use the screen's bitmap in the
CreateUpfrontLayer_() call, but I don't think that's the problem...

I'm using it for a hacky WB painting program I did, so I'm not too
worried about being 100% system-friendly ;)

Just noticed - it's set for my WB size, so be careful (well, it locks
up anyway, so it doesn't matter too much ;)

See ya,
-- 
<tsb>
<sb>James L Boyd - jamesboyd@all-hail.freeserve.co.uk
<sb>Member of Team *AMIGA*, and *Dogbert's New Ruling Class.*
<sb>Connected from Dundee, Scotland. 
<sb>(http://surf.to/all-hail/)
<tsb>

The most beautiful thing we can experience is the mysterious. It is 
the source of all true art and all science. He to whom this emotion 
is a stranger, who can no longer pause to wonder and stand rapt in 
awe, is as good as dead: his eyes are closed.
-- Albert Einstein

--BOUNDARY.1747960104.2
Content-Disposition: attachment; filename="Layers.asc"
Encoding: quoted-printable
Content-Description: Attempted layer creation.

*scr.Screen=3DLockPubScreen_(0)

If *scr

  *rp.RastPort=3D*scr\_RastPort

  If *rp

    *bm.BitMap=3D*rp\_BitMap

    If *bm

      DEFTYPE.Layer_Info *layerinfo

      Request "","About to create layer!","OK"

      *layerinfo=3DCreateUpfrontLayer_ (&*layerinfo,*bm,0,0,639,254,#LAYE=
RSMART,0)

      Request "","Created layer!","OK" ; *** FAILS! ***

      If *layerinfo
        DeleteLayer_ 0,*layerinfo
        Request "","Deleted layer!","OK"
      Else Request "","Failed to create layer!","OK"
      EndIf

    Else Request "","Didn't get bitmap!","OK"
    EndIf

  Else Request "","Couldn't get rastport!","OK"
  EndIf

UnlockPubScreen_ 0,*scr
Else Request "","Didn't lock pubscreen!","OK"
EndIf

End


--BOUNDARY.1747960104.2

