@NODE "Mail_601" "Re: Layers..."
 for scott@online.u-net.com; Mon, 5 Apr 1999 10:51:24 +0100
From: "Scott" <scott@assembler.free-online.co.uk>
Subject: Re: Layers...
Date: Mon, 5 Apr 1999 10:49:39 +0100
	boundary="----=_NextPart_000_000D_01BE7F52.0158DF80"

------=_NextPart_000_000D_01BE7F52.0158DF80
	charset="iso-8859-1"
Encoding: 7bit

Hello James,

On the 4th of April 1999, James L Boyd asked....


>Hi, 

>Can anyone tell me why this doesn't work?

>I know that I'm not supposed to use the screen's bitmap in the
>CreateUpfrontLayer_() call, but I don't think that's the problem...

I've attached a modified version of your code that works now (said with
fingers crossed!)  There were a couple of things wrong that I could see.
First, you need a *Layer type to call CreateUpfrontLayer_ with, not a
*Layer_Info.  Second, you need to tell the Layer_Info structure that you
are going to create a new layer, so you need a call to NewLayerInfo_().
This also means you need to DisposeLayerInfo_() as well.  Also, you
need to give CreateUpfrontLayer_ *Layer_Info, the pointer, not &*Layer_Info,
the address of the pointer.

Hmmm, I didn't explain that very well, but the code should work now.
I hope that it helps.


Regards,
Scott

scott@assembler.free-online.co.uk



