Hello James,

On the 6th of April 1999, James L Boyd asked...

>Well, it turns out that I don't want the layer stuff - I had the weird
>impression that layers were invisible/transparent for some strange reason :)

>Thanks to you and Dave for your help, but I'll tell you what I'm trying to
>do : I've made a stupid little WB drawing program (attached - hold both
>buttons to draw ;) but when you quit, it leaves its mess on the WB screen.

>This can be cleared by calling the Workbench Redraw All menu...so I'm trying
>to duplicate this before I quit...

>Anyone got any ideas?

Well, it's not much of an idea, but how about...

Window 1,0,0,*scr\Width,*scr\Height,$800,"",1,2
CloseWindow 1

...just before End.

It works.  Hardly elegant, but neither is drawing directly to the
Workbench Rastport  (o;

I'm sure someone else will reply with a single OS call to do it or
something, but I couldn't think of an easy way, so I hope this helps
in the meantime.


Regards,
Scott

scott@assembler.free-online.co.uk



