>
>Anyone got any ideas?


Hmmm..not really...you need a way to tell wb to refresh..ie, clean up it`s
bitmap...I don`t know of how you do that (though prefs which is a seperate
program..tells it to change screen size, and resetup it`s self...anyone know
how that is done..or is that another undisclosed system hack??)

>I found BeginUpdate_ in the autodocs and wondered if I could pass it the WB
>window's layer, get whatever that returns and update it somehow with that
(as
>you can see, I'm grasping at straws here :)


Umm...I think that`s when you do your own refresh for windows...ie, don`t
use smart refresh.

>OK, so it won't be the end of the world if no-one knows how to do it,
>but I would like to be able to just do this little courtesy before quitting
;)


What exactly does it need to do?? I remember fake wb dying program`s which
would clone the wb screen, and force it to stay at the front and then you
watch it drip down your screen...if you could lock the wb screen (lock pub
screen??) you could simply copy the bitmap (I think using friend bitmap type
to make sure it`d be chunky compatible and then use one of the blt commands
to store the original wb screen to restore). If you need to be able to draw
while wb is running normal..then you`ll have trouble...as your altering the
wb bitmap aswell as the system. (though I think rastports are the way to
go...they should be gfx card compatible..and a lot safer than using
bitmaps).

Good luck,

Dave




