@NODE "Mail_614" "List arrays..."
 for scott@online.u-net.com; Sun, 25 Apr 1999 20:46:22 +0000
From: Rick Hodger <rick.thehub@bigfoot.com>
Date: Sun, 25 Apr 1999 15:34:46 +0100
Organization: Pagan Software
Subject: List arrays...


In a program I'm doing at the moment, it uses a list array to store a flist
of files in the current directory, and whether they are dirs etc, the
newtype looks like this:

NEWTYPE .filelist
    dummy.w
    name$
    size.l
    dir.b
End NEWTYPE
Dim List dirs.filelist(1024)

Now, the problem is that after about filling, and clearing this list exactly
4 times, it refuses to clear any more and sticks to what was filled in the
2nd time.

This is just using "Clearlist dirs()" as "Dim List dirs.filelist(1024)"
which I have used in the past to clear arrays refuses and returns the error
"Unable to free memory" then quits the program.  Oh, and this is done
inside a statement.

Any help or ideas would be appreciated, and thanks in advance!

