@NODE "Mail_616" "Re: Lots of OS questions to feed on ;)"
 for scott@online.u-net.com; Wed, 21 Apr 1999 23:25:58 +0100
From: "Tony Rolfe" <edgewater@shoalhaven.net.au>
Organization: Edgewater Motel, Burrill Lake, NSW 2539 Australia
Date: 22 Apr 99 08:20:00 +1000
Subject: Re: Lots of OS questions to feed on ;)
Encoding: 7bit

On Wed, 21 Apr 1999 19:52:05 +0100 Rob Hutchinson said:
> 
> and lastly, <Phew>
> 
> 6, What is the best way to detect double-clicks in windows?

At last, a question I can understand (and answer)

Basically you need to do:

sSecs.l = 0   ; Time of last click in seconds
sMicros.l = 0 ; Time of last click in Micros

Repeat
   ev = WaitEvent
   If EventWindow = 1       ; Only process events for your window
      Select ev
         Case #IDCMP_MOUSEBUTTONS            ; Mouse button hit
            If MButtons = 1
               CurrentTime_ &eSecs.l,&eMicros.l
               If DoubleClick_(sSecs.l,sMicros.l,eSecs,eMicros)
                  << do your thing>>
               else
                   sSecs = eSecs
                   sMicros = eMicros
               endif
            endif
     end select
forever

Hope that helps.    Call again if I wasn't clear enough

Cheers

