@NODE "Mail_628" "Re: Me and my Blitz Programming Language"
 for scott@online.u-net.com; Fri, 30 Apr 1999 14:24:06 +0000
From: Donovan Reeve <bubby.lnk@ispi.net>
Date: Fri, 30 Apr 1999 07:19:55 +0500
Subject: Re: Me and my Blitz Programming Language

On 29-Apr-99, S9225796 flashed:
>I have subscribed to this mailing lost to ask anyone - how do I delete
>Blitz Basic off my hard drive ?

  Just the same way that you delete anything else, like Amos or C.

 -  In a text editor, load Sys:S/user-startup.  Remove all lines
    refering to Blitz Basic (there should be three lines all together).
    You can use Ted, the Blitz editor, the one you are going to delete
    for this.

 -  Save the user-startup file over the old one.

 -  Select the directory where you have it installed.

 -  Choose show all files from the window menue on your workbench.

 -  Click on each file once with the left mouse button while holding down
    the shift key so that they are all selected. Release the shift key.

 -  Choose Delete from the Icons menu on Workbench.  They're gone!



 - Reboot.  Your done.




bye,

Donovan Reeve (bubby.lnk@ispi.net)



