@NODE "Mail_630" "Mega-Anim-Player (Practical Test)"
 for scott@online.u-net.com; Sun, 11 Apr 1999 23:53:44 +0100
From: Jamie Bentley <sniper@technet2000.com.au>
Date: Sun, 08 Jan 1978 15:57:47 +0500
Organization: Sniper Productions
Subject: Mega-Anim-Player (Practical Test)

 Heyas,

 I'm no programmer (I won't deny it), but I would like to know how hard it
would be to have a simple IFF-Anim8 (possibly Anim5) animation player that ran
off HD (12 frames per second) running a 256 colour screen (different palette
each frame, standard animation stuff) but only at a resolution of 160x128?

 Not only this, how hard would it be to "Double" the size of the anim (made
the pixels 2x2)?

 In a nut shell:

 * HD Anim5 or Anim8 at 160x128 at x2 with 256 colours... Possibly with a mod
playing in the background.

 I look forward to a reply :)

 Jamie Bentley


