@NODE "Mail_631" "Re: Mega-Anim-Player (Practical Test)"
 for scott@online.u-net.com; Mon, 12 Apr 1999 12:26:15 +0000
From: "Paul" <paulwest@stationone.demon.co.uk>
Organization: private
Date: 12 Apr 99 12:10:21 +0000
Subject: Re: Mega-Anim-Player (Practical Test)
Encoding: 7bit

Jamie,
 
>  I'm no programmer (I won't deny it),

Then what are you doing here? ;-P

> but I would like to know how hard it
> would be to have a simple IFF-Anim8 (possibly Anim5) animation player that ran
> off HD (12 frames per second) running a 256 colour screen (different palette
> each frame, standard animation stuff) but only at a resolution of 160x128?

You could use any pd anim player to do that. But to do it from blitz
is another matter entirely. You can use the RIAnim library which
allows you to play anim5 and anim7 but not anim8, and the whole anim
has to be loaded into memory first. The playback speed you're after
should be no problem even on an 020 I'd imagine.
 
>  Not only this, how hard would it be to "Double" the size of the anim (made
> the pixels 2x2)?

Would need some assembler routine i figure.

-- 
Paul.

