@NODE "Mail_635" "Re: MIDI Question :)"
 for scott@online.u-net.com; Tue, 20 Apr 1999 23:23:40 +0000
Date: Tue, 20 Apr 1999 19:22:36 -0300 (ADT)
Sender: ah210@chebucto.ns.ca
From:	John Mason <ah210@chebucto.ns.ca>
Subject: Re: MIDI Question :)

Hello Rui,

> How many devices can you hook up into a midi port?
> Is it like SCSI, one device hooked up on to the other or is it 1 port 1 device?

It depends, as with most things.  MIDI devices usually have two or three
ports, IN, OUT, and sometimes THRU.  The IN port accepts input, obviously.
The OUT port sends output from that device only, so data from other
devices is not sent out this port.  THRU outputs the data that this device
is seeing at its input, so you can use THRU to continue on to the next
device.  THRU doesn't send any of the data generated by this device
though.

Hope this helps,


	|   John Mason  :  chebucto.ns.ca@ah210   | 
	| Amiga 1200 020/882 3.0 10MB RAM 810M HD |
