@NODE "Mail_643" "Re: Mildred Trouble"
 for scott@online.u-net.com; Wed, 7 Apr 1999 18:35:44 +0100
From: "Paul" <paulwest@stationone.demon.co.uk>
Organization: private
Date: 7 Apr 99 18:33:04 +0000
Subject: Re: Mildred Trouble
Encoding: 7bit

>     I have recently decided to start using Mildred in my programs. However, I
> am having some trouble with the examples that I have downloaded. Could
> someone give me an example of how to simply open a screen with a bitmap in
> the background and animate a shape with MQBlit?

on the fly...

WBStartup
InitBank 0,320*240,$10002
CludgeBitmap 0,320,240,8,Bank(0)
InitPalette 0,256
LoadBitmap 0,"Background.IFF",0
Screen 0,0,0,320,240,8,0,"demo",0,0,0
ShowPalette 0
Mc2pWindow 0,320,240
MBitmap 0,320,240
MPlanar16ToBitmap 0,Bank(0)
LoadBitmap 0,"Shape.IFF"
MShape 0,32,32
MPlanar16ToShape 0,Bank(0),32,32,320,240
MMakeCookie 0
MBitmap 1,320,240
MBlockScroll 0,0,320,240,0,0,0
MQueue 0,1 ; 1 shape
Repeat
  xpos=SMouseX
  ypos=SMouseY
  MQBlit 0,min(xpos,320-32),min(ypos,240-32)
  Mc2p Bank(0)
  MUnQueue 0,0
Until Joyb(0)>0
End

tralala, it's something like that (dont hold me to it). Background
image should be 320x240 IFF and the shape image should be 32x32 IFF.
You should get the idea, it's not very difficult to animate, just have
more shapes and change the shape number.


-- 
Paul.

