> I have been trying to write a program in mildred that scrolls around on a
> large bitmap and qblits shapes on top of it. I can do both in separate
> programs but I can't seem to get both things to work in one program. What
> should the basic format of a program like this be? (eg:open chunky bitmap,
> convert to planar, open chunky bitmap, blit shapes, convert to planar, etc.)
> If someone has an example of this it would be greatly appreciated. Also, is
> it better to use banks or Allocmem? The scrolling demo by Mikkel Loekke uses
> Allocmem, while most of the others I have seen use banks. The manual says
> something like "we advise programmers to use banks instead of allocmem" or
> something like that. Why is this?

Well all you really need do is something like...

Open planar bitmap
load in background to planar bitmap
Open chunky bitmap
Convert planar to chunky bitmap
load in shape to planar bitmap
open chunky shape
convert planar to chunky shape
copy chunky bitmap to second chunky bitmap (for background store)
loop
  mqblit shape onto first chunky bitmap
  mc2p first chunky bitmap to planar
  munqueue using second chunky bitmap
next loop

something like that.

I only use banks because it's a little easier to keep track of than
having to define extra variables to hold the mem pointers. Ease of use
really.
-- 
Paul.

