You would need to use OpenLocale_ to get a pointer. Don't know what string=
 
you'd pass as the locale though.

I think the locale name is like the name of the area you are in, and the 
language is the current language you are using. For example, if you lived =
in a 
country called Timbuctoo (the locale), your language might be timbuctese. =
Not 
the same string basically.


