@NODE "Mail_666" "More Mildred Questions"
 for scott@online.u-net.com; Fri, 9 Apr 1999 18:41:26 +0100
From: Jake Frederick <gonzo@acadia.net>
Date: Fri, 09 Apr 1999 12:41:50 +0500
Subject: More Mildred Questions

--BOUNDARY.19752456.2

    Included is a short program based on some code that Paul West sent me. I
am trying to have a background bitmap that is constantly changing with a
shape blitted on top of it. Is this the most memory efficient way to do it?
Also, the code I have grabs a shape from the first bitmap but I want to take
the shape from a shapes file. What am I doing wrong? 

-- 
-If the doors of perception were cleansed everything would appear to man as
it
truly is, infinite.-

--BOUNDARY.19752456.2
Content-Disposition: attachment; filename="mildredtest"
Encoding: quoted-printable


background=3D1

WBStartup
NoCli

MCPU MProcessor
Mc2pCPUmode MProcessor

MReserveBitmaps 20
MReservec2pWindows 1

Data$ "blitz2:work/3dtest/4.b","blitz2:work/3dtest/5.b","blitz2:work/3dte=
st/6.b"
Data$ "blitz2:work/3dtest/4.b","blitz2:work/3dtest/5.b","blitz2:work/3dte=
st/6.b"

InitBank 0,320*200,$10002
CludgeBitMap 0,320,200,8,Bank(0)
MBitmap 0,320,200

For n=3D1 To 6
  Read pic$
  CludgeBitMap n,320,200,8,Bank(0)
  LoadBitMap n,pic$
  MBitmap n,320,200
  MPlanar16ToBitmap n,Bank(0)
Next

InitPalette 0,256
LoadPalette 0,"blitz2:work/3dtest/1.b",0
Screen 0,0,0,320,200,8,0,"demo",0,0,0
ShowPalette 0

Mc2pWindow 0,320,200
MBitmap 0,320,200
MPlanar16ToBitmap 0,Bank(0)
LoadShapes 0,"blitz2:gfx/nin.shapes"
MShape 0,42,100
MPlanar16ToShape 0,Bank(0),42,100,320,200
MMakeCookie 0
MQueue 0,1 ; 1 shape

While RawStatus($45)=3DFalse

  background+1
  If background>6 Then background=3D1

  MBlockScroll 0,0,320,200,0,0,background

  xpos=3DSMouseX
  ypos=3DSMouseY
  MQBlit 0,Min(xpos,320-42),Min(ypos,200-100)
  Mc2p Bank(0)
  MUnQueue 0,0

Wend





--BOUNDARY.19752456.2

