@NODE "Mail_669" "SV: More Mildred Questions"
 for scott@online.u-net.com; Fri, 9 Apr 1999 20:39:19 +0100
From: "Andreas Hĺkansson" <andy.h@telia.com>
Subject: SV: More Mildred Questions
Date: Fri, 9 Apr 1999 21:38:27 +0200


>So it would be quicker and just as easy to just load a bitmap and grab the
>shapes rather than load the shapes, blit them and then grab them right? A
>shapes file probably takes up less room than a bitmap doesn't it?


What paul means is that you need to convert your standard blitz shapes into
chunky shapes. This is only needed one time, since you can save your chunky
chapes in a memory bank or simular, and then reload them using mcludgeshape
or what ever that command is called =) Mikkel Lokke wrote an example on
how to use cludeshapes with mildred. It's on the mildred page and you should
have a look at it. I dont think that example shows you how to store your
chunkyshapes
in a file, but that shouldnt be to hard for you to figure out.

 ByE!



