I watched as Rob Hutchinson hammered "More OctaMED SoundStudio stuff.." out
on their keyboard...

>   Ok,.. I got a ikle bit bored and did some more work on the OSS stuff..

> I`m just wondering if anyone who tried the other example can tell WTF
> the attach gives you the most pretty GURU`s you ever seen in your life ;)
> ehehehehe....

> I`ve byterun checked the mem locations for the MMD3 header, and they
> are both at the offset of the address, (IE, the LoadModule_FastM_
> command doesn`t append any sort of structure before the module giving
> it`s length and such....

> I`m just wondering if INCBIN decodes the raw binary into chipmem??? It
> shouldnt do, but if it does this could be the prob, otherwise I have no
> other ideas except that perhaps LoadModule_FastM_ suffixes data to
> the end of the module at the mem address....

> I know this is a bit far fetched (maybe) but anyone got any ideas?

Okay, mine'd go like this:

XINCLUDE "BlitzLibs:MEDFuncs.bb2"

If CheckMEDLibs{}=True ; check the needed libs are available
    If MEDLoad{0,"work:oss.sunrise"}=True ; Load the module and check the
format
        If InitMEDLibs{0,medinfo(1)\modtype[0]}=True ; Init the proper lib
            MEDPlay{0} ; Play the med :)    
        Endif
    Endif
Endif

Much simpler :)

Oh, and BTW, the libs contain functions for checking which player you need
plus a fixed version of your source, a very silly mistake indeed.  Did you
not read the docs? :)

But it's still bugged, it screws up when you quit.  And I know it isn't the
FreePlayerM_, you wanna put a "End" after the Incbin part? :)

