@NODE "Mail_681" "Mr Mouse and the 060 jerk."
 for scott@online.u-net.com; Mon, 12 Apr 1999 19:38:45 +0100
Date: Mon, 12 Apr 1999 19:18:40 +0100
From: BaH <brucey@thenet.co.uk>
Subject: Mr Mouse and the 060 jerk.

Actually, it's nothing to do with power, it's all to do with the 060
emulating the FPU instructions, as described in the Cyberpatcher
documentation...

"...Unknown instructions cause a trap and during the trap the emulation (of
the 6888x fpu) has to find the right emulation routine and run its
function.  In a trap the processor is in supervisor mode and no other tasks
can run.
This effect is visible by a not smooth running mouse...the system gets
almost unusable the more unimplemented instructions are used by a program.
Cyberpatcher tries to patch the most used instructions that have to be
emulated"


Just a thought....
..and I could be completely wrong.

Brucey

          ( BaH )
         O
        o         PowerMac 6500/250 64mb 10gigHD ZIP100 Jaz2
 ____^_o          Amiga 1260T/50 18mb 4.65gigHD's ZIP100 CD
