@NODE "Mail_684" "Re: Mr Mouse and the 060 jerk."
 for scott@online.u-net.com; Tue, 13 Apr 1999 09:33:14 +0100
From: "David McMinn" <D.Mcminn@eee.rgu.ac.uk>
Organization: The Robert Gordon University, E&EE
Date: Tue, 13 Apr 1999 09:30:32 +0100
encoding: Quoted-printable
Subject: Re: Mr Mouse and the 060 jerk.

> After reading your comment about the 060 emulating the FPU instructions,=
 I
> went to Motorola's web page and read that the M68EC060 emulates the FPU
> and MMU. I believe if you have a M68060RC, there is no emulation needed.
> Is this correct?

 No, the full 060 needs to emulate some 68881 and 68882 FPU instructions.

Speaking of other 060 variants, I think its either Power or Eyetech or som=
eone 
like that are selling a low cost 060 board, and they're using an LC060 run=
ning 
at 75MHz (which doesn't have an FPU at all!).

 According to M's website, it does 113 MIPS at that speed (yes we all beli=
eve 
that).


