@NODE "Mail_686" "MUI NLISTLIEW"
 for scott@online.u-net.com; Thu, 8 Apr 1999 21:27:23 +0000
From: Andrew Wheeler <apwheeler@apwheeler.demon.co.uk>
Date: Thu, 08 Apr 1999 22:27:40 +0100
Subject: MUI NLISTLIEW

Hi,

Help me before all my hair falls out.  I am in need of desperate help of
setting up a list for use in Nlistview class.  At the moment The list I have
is:

Dim List *hello.l(50)

*hello.l(0)=Null("hello")

f.l=AddItem(*hello.l())

*hello.l(1)=Null("bob")

f.l=AddItem(*hello.l())

*hello.l(2)=Null("bob2")

f.l=AddItem(*hello.l())


MUIAddTags 2,#MUIA_NList_SourceArray,&*hello.l(0)

MUINewObject 1,"NList.mcc",0
MUINewObject 2,"NListview.mcc",1

All the items appear in the NListview,  but between them are a load of rubbish
2 lines of funny character codes and symbols between each line.  Please
somebody must be able to help me!! please!

Also is there a way of increasing the stack size for programs you run from
blitz, at the moment I am having to create an execute and run that because
the stack space is not great enough for Nlistview Class wehn compiled/run
from blitz!!

PLEASE HELP ( You will be my best m8 for live if you can)

Oh, and does anyone know where I can get the Autodoc and include for
ListTree.Mcc, It doesn#t matter if the include is in C format, I can convert
it!

THanx 

Yours Sincerely
-- 
A.Wheeler

