@NODE "Mail_691" "MUIListView problems :("
 for scott@online.u-net.com; Tue, 13 Apr 1999 13:37:34 +0100
From: "Matt Briggs" <s9225796@rothervalley.ac.uk>
Subject: MUIListView problems :(
Date: Tue, 13 Apr 1999 13:35:24 +0100
	charset="iso-8859-1"
Encoding: 7bit

Hello all.

I'm currently using the outstanding EF Magic User Interface library for
Blitz
Basic II, which I discovered a few weeks ago on the Aminet and I have
been fliddling around with MUI now for quite sometime, however I am
currently having a few problems with the MUIListview, which I would be most
greatful if someone could possibly help me with :)

Firstly, I am using the command `MUIInsertSingle' to insert lines into the
listview, however when ever the window is resized the listview contents are
lost. Is it possible therefore to overcome this.

Secondly, When I try to display an image in the listview using the escape
key followed by ` i[5: ' and a picture name + ] it only displays the top
half of the image according to the font height. The rest of the image is cut
off by the text below. I therefore need to know the tag(s) or command etc.
to enable me to display the entire image in a list view.

Thanx for all your help.

Best regards,
Matthew Briggs


