@NODE "Mail_697" "NewStuff now available! (A little off topic)"
 for scott@online.u-net.com; Sun, 11 Apr 1999 03:35:48 +0100
Date:	Sat, 10 Apr 1999 23:34:21 -0300 (ADT)
Sender: ah210@chebucto.ns.ca
From:	John Mason <ah210@chebucto.ns.ca>
Subject: NewStuff now available! (A little off topic)

Hi all,
  
  My latest project, NewStuff, is now available, exclusively to Blitzers,
as a prerelease before I upload it to Aminet.  That way only a few dozen
people or so will suffer massive hard drive failures as I work out any
remaining bugs... :)  Just kidding!  

NewStuff is a (Blitz) little program to keep track of new files that have
arrived in a directory on your hard drive -- it's great if you've ever
downloaded something and had trouble finding it later.  Please give it a
try, but make sure you read the docs first!  

The URL:  http://chebucto.ns.ca/~ah210/nsform.html

You just need to fill out the form on this page (so I know how many people
have tried it) and you'll be taken to the download page.

Thanks, and have fun!


