@NODE "Mail_718" "Re: offsets shapes"
 for scott@online.u-net.com; Sun, 18 Apr 1999 18:09:15 +0100
From: "David McMinn" <D.Mcminn@eee.rgu.ac.uk>
Organization: The Robert Gordon University, E&EE
Date: Sun, 18 Apr 1999 18:07:47 +0100
encoding: Quoted-printable
Subject: Re: offsets shapes

> I was not refering to the amigalibs.res file but how can you include
> other files for example if i was to use the cybergraphics library you ge=
t
> a .res file when you download it but if you convert librarys into blitz
> using newfdconvert it creates the library but you can not use the offset
> values for the library because there is no .res file.
> 
> How do you convert them or create them for use in blitz.

Sorry my mistake. Fred wrote OpenBlitz, which converts C and C++ header fi=
les 
(.h) into Blitz. They are the files that basically make up the .res files,=
 
although they are witten in C, so use OpenBlitz (which doesn't convert soe=
m 
things) or do it by hand. Then make a resident file from the resulting Bli=
tz 
files, as you would normally.

 However, if you need to include the amigalibs.res file when you are creat=
ing 
the .res file, you will end up with a file which has amigalibs.res + your =
new 
stuff. So it might be better to not do that, but use XINCLUDE instead.


