@NODE "Mail_738" "Re: Overflow Errors"
 for scott@online.u-net.com; Tue, 27 Apr 1999 09:48:06 +0100
From: "David McMinn" <D.Mcminn@eee.rgu.ac.uk>
Organization: The Robert Gordon University, E&EE
Date: Tue, 27 Apr 1999 09:45:52 +0100
encoding: Quoted-printable
Subject: Re: Overflow Errors

> *Gadget\Flags & ($ffff-#GFLG_TABCYCLE)   which gave me an overflow error=
. 

If you are trying to clear a bit in some flag bits, then its better to use=
 
*Gadget\Flags & NOT(#GFLG_TABCYCLE), you avoid all those nasty (un)signed 
problems, and its easier to see whats going on.


