@NODE "Mail_739" "Re: Overflow Errors"
 for scott@online.u-net.com; Tue, 27 Apr 1999 13:46:25 +0100
From: Curt Esser <camge@ix.netcom.com>
Date: Tue, 27 Apr 1999 07:30:34 -0500
Subject: Re: Overflow Errors

Hi Tony

On 27-Apr-99, Tony Rolfe wrote:

> I Actually meant Fred.w & ($ffff - #SomeFlag), trying to set the flag
> value off without changing the other flags.
> 
> I meant that I need negative values for other variables in my program
> so I can't just set Overflow Errors off.

Yes, you can.  It won't hurt the variables at all, it just prevents the
error requester when the debugger is on.  I ALWAYS leave Overflow Errors off
and I use many negative values.  

Just remember that Blitz always reads them as signed, so you have to do the
& thing to read them as unsigned.   

> Why oh why doesn't Blitz have a signed/unsigned
> option on the DEFTYPE command??.

I have often wondered about that myself.

                                    Yours electronically,
                                    Curt Esser
                                    camge@ix.netcom.com
                                    http://members.xoom.com/Curt_Esser/



