BTW, The playstation had a Data Decompression Engine (MDEC) which
did video decompression in hardware. It was described as a Motion
JPEG Decompressor operating at 80 MIPS directly connected to the
CPU bus with 132 MB/second of bandwidth. That kind of thing can`t
really be compared with anything the Amiga has to offer and in
fact even now when the PlayStation is looking very much outdated,
it still manages to play FMV's better than most.

Cheers,

Paul

