Well in fact it is just as correct behaviour as it can get, but everybody=

seams to forget that. :)

Oh and if you want small trick for using cosine/sine in your own angle
systems you can reverse so that you use sine when normaly cosine is used
and negated cosine when normaly sine is used.

this will give you a coordinate system where angle 0 will point to up and=

the rotation goes anticlock wise as it's suposed to.

