@NODE "Mail_773" "Re: Randomize EEEEK!"
 for scott@online.u-net.com; Wed, 28 Apr 1999 14:01:27 +0100
From: "Paul" <paulwest@stationone.demon.co.uk>
Organization: private
Date: 28 Apr 99 13:58:28 +0000
Subject: Re: Randomize EEEEK!
Encoding: 7bit

> Well I thought it was a clever way to do it ;)
> But if you try that you will see that it averages at around 1000000
> +/- a couple of hundred-thousand :((.. Never goes anywhere near
> 0 or 2000000... Which is really dodgy...
> 
> Anyone got ANY ideas at all? Pleeeeeeez..

If RND only returns word values it may be that part of the randomizing
routine is the same as used for quick values. One suggestion to make
two RND's into a longword would be...

Num.l=(Rnd(65535) LSL 16)+Rnd(65535)

but then you dont have much control over the upper bound of the
numbers.

-- 
Paul.

