 for scott@online.u-net.com; Sun, 4 Apr 1999 20:30:15 +0100
From: "Dave" <dave@nbsamiga.demon.co.uk>
Subject: Recursive directories and bug fixed dll :)
Date: Sun, 4 Apr 1999 20:22:10 +0100
	boundary="----=_NextPart_000_0020_01BE7ED8.D40E5F60"

------=_NextPart_000_0020_01BE7ED8.D40E5F60
	charset="iso-8859-1"
Encoding: 7bit

Hi Jamie,

 Here`s an example of a recursive directory and my dynamic lists...there are
a few things it does...and if you need a hand messing with it..feel free to
email me. (it`s not the least memory using program I could have created, but
it does work, and took me 10 mins)

And included is the very last version of DLL that I`ll post to the
list..maybe I`ll find a place for it, if I ever get around to doing a new
web page...(maybe you can put it on your site rui??). There was a bug in the
last one (if you cleared an empty list, the list got stuck...which is now
fixed) plus the dllsort include is included, and the
updated docs. (the dir example is quite good, you could even sort it for
filenames/dirnames, and/or split the files and dirs).

Good luck, and happy hunting,

Dave




