@NODE "Mail_784" "Recursive directories and dynamic data storage"
 for scott@online.u-net.com; Sat, 3 Apr 1999 16:41:35 +0100
X-Originating-IP: [195.92.194.13]
From: "Jamie Solomons" <jamiesblitz@hotmail.com>
Subject: Recursive directories and dynamic data storage
Date: Sat, 03 Apr 1999 07:40:19 PST

Hi Everyone
Does anyone know of a way to do dynamic data storage? I.E. something 
like dynamic arrays? I need this for recursive directory scanning. i 
need to store the paths of sub directorys but I don't know how many 
directories I will need to store. Any help on this subject would be very 
gratefully recieved. If anyone has an example of recursive directory 
scanning then it would be very helpful. At the moment I am using the 
follow (rather crude) system:

1) scan the first DIR
2) add the paths of all sub directories to the list (string array or 
whatever)
3) go through the list from top to bottom, scanning each directory on 
the list and adding the path of any DIRs to the end of the list.
4) continue going through the list until complete (i.e. you've got to 
the bottom of the list)

I hope I have explained this properly. It's a bit difficult to explain. 
If anyone has a better was of doing this then it would help a lot! :)

Thanks very much,

Regards,
Jamie Solomons

