Have you tried passing 0 (zero) instead of a string to the tag for the
path?? (I haven`t tested this..just a guess, that would maybe just use the
current cd instead). I don`t think you mean root do you?? the root is the
bit before the : in a path (ie, ram:t/temp the root is ram:)...if you just
need the root, you`ll have to check the current full path and hunt the root
down yourself and then pass this to asl.

Just an idea,

Dave



