@NODE "Mail_793" "Re: root"
 for scott@online.u-net.com; Wed, 28 Apr 1999 11:17:22 +0100
From: Curt Esser <camge@ix.netcom.com>
Date: Wed, 28 Apr 1999 04:56:21 -0500
Subject: Re: root

--BOUNDARY.1748611912.2

Hi amorel

On 27-Apr-99, amorel wrote:
> As noone answered i resent it, wishfull thinking ;-)
> 
> How do I get an asl requester to open on the root(assign or volume list), 
> besides giving a non existant path entry(which makes the screen flash).

Here is a way to get it to open on the root directory of whatever device it
was run from.  Thanks to a function I found in James Boyd's StatsFuncts
file   ;)

Later...
-- 

                                    Yours electronically,
                                    Curt Esser
                                    camge@ix.netcom.com
                                    http://members.xoom.com/Curt_Esser/


--BOUNDARY.1748611912.2
Content-Disposition: attachment; filename="RootReq.asc"


;make this into an exec and try sticking it in different
;places and running it.  It should always find the root
;directory of the device it was run from

;--------------------------------------------------------------
; Function : ProgsDir {}

; Author : Nick Clover - nick@bauk.freeserve.co.uk

; Returns a string with the program's directory.

; IMPORTANT! Only works with compiled executables,as
; Compiling & Running doesn't use a directory (obviously ;)

Function.s ProgsDir{}

  MaxLen path$=200
  NameFromLock_ GetProgramDir_(),&path$,200
  path$=Peek$(&path$)
  If Right$(path$,1)<>":" AND Right$(path$,1)<>"/"
    path$+"/"
  EndIf
Function Return path$
End Function
;--------------------------------------------------------------

Function$ FindRoot{fullpath$}  ;returns the root directory name
  stopat.w=Instr(fullpath$,":")
  root$=Left$(fullpath$,stopat)
  Function Return root$
End Function

;--------------------------------------------------------------

WBStartup
WBenchToFront_
FindScreen 0

MaxLen pa$=255         ;for the ASLrequester
MaxLen fi$=255

ourpath$=ProgsDir{}    ;get our full path

pa$=FindRoot{ourpath$} ;set default path to the root directory

dummy$=ASLFileRequest$ ("Test",pa$,fi$)

End



--BOUNDARY.1748611912.2

