@NODE "Mail_826" "Re: string compression"
 for scott@online.u-net.com; Tue, 13 Apr 1999 18:10:18 +0000
From: "Dave" <dave@nbsamiga.demon.co.uk>
Subject: Re: string compression
Date: Tue, 13 Apr 1999 18:08:29 +0100
	charset="iso-8859-1"
Encoding: 7bit

Btw...forgot to mention...it`s the norm when compressing raw bytes with lzw
to say

any compressed value under 256 is a raw byte

any compressed value over 255 is an offset in the table (ie, compressed
value-256 table pos)

that helps for some speed ups, and lets you off the first 256 table
entries....


Just remembered that ;),

Dave


P.s. it doesn`t make the table size any bigger, as your the compressed data
still has to have the 256 byte values in the compressed bit size! (ie, you
still have to have 256 raw bytes in the possible compressed values 0-4096
for example!)





