> 
> This can have some very good compression ratios indeed :) 4.5k to 800 bytes

Yes this does work and it's a part of what I'm doing already. The
problem I have is that, for example, you have one pixel that is a
different colour, /followed by/ a sequence of pixels the same colour.
The byterun routine would just think that no sequence was possible and
so the repetition searcher would then start looking for enormous long
strings starting with one colour and carrying on with another. I have
however implemented a threshold now for how many adjacent equally
coloured pixels are allowed within the repetition before the search
stops, which helps speed enormously if it's set carefully.

-- 
Paul.

