From: "David McMinn" <D.Mcminn@eee.rgu.ac.uk>
Organization: The Robert Gordon University, E&EE
Date: Thu, 8 Apr 1999 18:32:44 +0100
encoding: Quoted-printable
Subject: Re: system calls

> I am developing Asm functions, and I want to use system calls inside. Fo=
r
> example, I use Open with name address in d1 and mode in d2. But it doesn=
't
> work with Copymem (I write JSR -324(a6) with exec base in a6 (=3D 4)). T=
he
> debugger stops and say : "GURU - Illegal instruction". What is the probl=
em
> ?

exec base is not 4. The address of the lib base is Peek.l(4), in ASM would=
 be 
something like:
    MOVE.l 4,a6

> I also read in the lib dev doc we should use ALibJsr with tokens of the
> system functions. But where are these tokens ?

I think it means to do
    ALibJsr CopyMem_


