@NODE "Mail_864" "Task List Questions"
 for scott@online.u-net.com; Sun, 4 Apr 1999 15:32:52 +0100
From: bml@thenet.co.uk (Simon Archer)
X-FTN-To: Simon Hitchen
Subject: Task List Questions
Date: 04 Apr 1999 15:29:05
X-newsreader: Spot 1.3b #1534
encoding: quoted-printable

On 4 Apr 99 Simon Hitchen wrote about 'Task List Questions'.

 SH>   FindTask_(&TASKNAME$)  Doesn't seem to work when a task has been
 SH> launched from a CLI.

No, it wont, programs launched from CLI are Processes, not Tasks. Currently
there is no standard mechanism for finding processes.

If you are going to traverse the exec task list, you must enclose the loop
between a Forbid()/Permit() pair. And the safest way to to it is to copy th=
e
task list into a list of your own, then you can Permit() and work through
your own list without worry.

You'll need to check out the CLI structure in order to obtain the process=
 name.

Simon Archer


