> *task.Task = *node. There'll be flags there somewhere, check how to find out 
> what flag says that this task is actually a process. If it is a process then 
> you can safely say that the task newtype is part of the process one, so do 
> *process.Process = *task. Then within that there's a BCPL pointer to a 
> CommandLineInterface structure (BCPL pointers are longword aligned, so you need 
> to multiply it by 4 before getting the real pointer). Inside the 
> CommandLineInterface newtype there's a program name field. Use it. No code 
> though.

Been doing a few experiments with that code you posted :-)

Seem to have sorted out tasks from processes (the output agrees with
the output from ARTM)

I need guidance with the "BCPL pointer" thingy and the
CommandLineInterface structure parts tho.... Any ideas?


; Description:  Lists the tasks running and waiting
; Type:         System

Forbid_
*e.ExecBase = Peek.l(4)

NPrint"List of tasks waiting"
*node.Node = *e\TaskWait\lh_Head
While *node\ln_Succ
    Print Peek$(*node\ln_Name)

    ; Tasks seem to have flags %0001
    ; And Processes have flags %1101
    ; So the next bit sorts them out

    If *node\ln_Type AND 12
      NPrint " = Process"

      ; If it's a process, is the next line OK?

      *pro.Process = *node

      ; If it is, what to do next??
      ; something like:
      ; *cli.CommandLineInterface = *pro\ <dunno ?>

    Else
      NPrint " = Task"
    End If
    *node=*node\ln_Succ
Wend

NPrint ""
NPrint ""

NPrint "list of tasks ready to run"
*node.Node = *e\TaskReady\lh_Head
While *node\ln_Succ
    NPrint Peek$(*node\ln_Name)
    *node=*node\ln_Succ
Wend
Permit_

While Joyb(0)<>2
  WaitTOF_
Wend

End



-- 

Bye f'now

Simon

