@NODE "Mail_872" "Re: Task List Questions"
 for scott@online.u-net.com; Mon, 5 Apr 1999 13:49:17 +0100
From: "David McMinn" <D.Mcminn@eee.rgu.ac.uk>
Organization: The Robert Gordon University, E&EE
Date: Mon, 5 Apr 1999 13:47:26 +0100
encoding: Quoted-printable
Subject: Re: Task List Questions

Hi Simon

> I need guidance with the "BCPL pointer" thingy and the
> CommandLineInterface structure parts tho.... Any ideas?

 Yep indeedy. I've had a quick flick rthrough the OS includes:

>     If *node\ln_Type AND 12

Change this to: If *node\ln_Type =3D #NT_PROCESS
(or #NT_TASK for tasks)

>       ; If it's a process, is the next line OK?
> 

 Yeah, blank lines are nearly always OK in Blitz. Oh you meant...

>       *pro.Process =3D *node

 Thats fine too.

>       ; If it is, what to do next??
>       ; something like:
>       ; *cli.CommandLineInterface =3D *pro\ <dunno ?>

If *pro\pr_CLI
    *cli.CommandLineInterface =3D *pro\pr_CLI * 4
    If *cli\cli_CommandName
        NPrint Peek$(*cli\cli_CommandName * 4 + 1)
        ; Another BCPL pointer, to a string. BCPL strings have the
        ; length in the first byte, then the string afterwards,
        ; hence the +1
    End If
End If


