On 06-Apr-99, David McMinn wrote.

>  >   Ok, this is always something that's bugged me :-) - what's the
>  > difference between a task and a process?
>  =

>   Apart from the different structures? I think a task doesn't use any D=
OS =

>  functions, something like that.
>  =

>   Anyone who knows what they're speaking about want to jump in here?

Well Tasks are NOT allowed to use DOS.library calls!
started from OS 3.x Tasks are allowed to use certain functions from the
other libraries which might call DOS.library. Execs openlibrary have alwa=
ys
been allowed, but there are some others, which are documented in the AD's=
=2E

