Hi Folks,

I know I've been silen for a while, but I'm back now and I've got a
real treat for all those of you who love coding.

My new OS.

THIS IS ONLY A PREVIEW, IT'S NOT EVEN A BETA

It consists of Two files:

A Bootstrap file, which boots the Kernel.68k

and

A Kernel file, this must be in ram:

The Source code to the kernel is also provided so that you can tell me
your suggestions and try building your own OS, if you like.
I will be relesing my Boot strap memory map soon so any of you can
build your own kernel to be booted unsing my boot strap.

please note, that none of the OS Function calls have been included in
the kernel yet, as I'm still deciding which should be included.
This is not the final kernel structure, it's simply a protokernel.

My OS will Consist of a basic Hardware specific Kernel and then there
will be Amiga style shared libries on top so that software can
interact with the kernel, which will in turn interact with the
hardware, The current Kernel is for 68K AGA amigas, but future
versions will allow PPC and Gfx cards.

Tell me what you think,


Thanx

Matt P.


