@NODE "Mail_887" "Re: Try My new OS, partially developed using Blitz"
 for scott@online.u-net.com; Tue, 20 Apr 1999 14:55:23 +0100
From: "Evan Tuer" <et@enterprise.net>
Organization: !
Date: 20 Apr 99 11:49:01 +0100
Subject: Re: Try My new OS, partially developed using Blitz
Encoding: 7bit


> My OS will Consist of a basic Hardware specific Kernel and then there
> will be Amiga style shared libries on top so that software can
> interact with the kernel, which will in turn interact with the
> hardware, The current Kernel is for 68K AGA amigas, but future
> versions will allow PPC and Gfx cards.
> 
> Tell me what you think,

Woohoo, pretty cool.  Make memory protection and virtual memory
support built in.. make the kernel <3k in size, make
executive-style multitasking scheduling..

Then release the sourcecode :)

PS it worked!

