@NODE "Mail_897" "Re: Video compression"
 for scott@online.u-net.com; Sun, 18 Apr 1999 03:19:45 +0100
From: "Dave" <dave@nbsamiga.demon.co.uk>
Subject: Re: Video compression
Date: Sun, 18 Apr 1999 03:19:47 +0100
	charset="iso-8859-1"
Encoding: 7bit

>
>  Is it a bit like HAM encoding?


HAM?? HOW DARE YOU.....lol.....ummm..not really..unless you want to go and
tell all those boffins at www.mpeg.org that they are using HAM....basically,
through reading lots of boring and silly docs..I found that YUV is one of
the prefered methods of video encoding, and a YUV 4:2:2 is comonly used in
MPEG encoding, so I simply up`d the YUV encoding to include horizontal
(that`s where my 2x2 square comes from) as well, so I can decompress enough
data in real time on the miggy. Well, that`s the theory anyway. And I
figured that with motion (ie, not changing dramitcally from one scene to
another) wouldn`t look too bad....only still frames would look bad (blocky)
if they stayed still for a long time. And it blur edges, so you end up with
uneven (ie, wobbly) edges...but I think I can put up with that for hitting
my spec :)

Dave




