Mathias PARNAUDEAU wrote:
> 
> is it possible to get the view mode of an opened screen ? We chose
> it when we open a screen (#SA_DisplayID tag) but I need to find
> it again.

What happened, did you forget it? ;)

I was sure this could be done quite easily and I was even sure that
I had some source that does this. However, I couldn`t find anything
that did this and was unable to locate the necessary info.

Perhaps you don`t really need this exact function. The only time
I think it might be usefull would be for a diagnostics tool or
perhaps you want to show the user which mode they are using. Usually
you would't care about the exact screen mode. You only usually
need to know if you got the correct size and depth. Sometimes
it can also be usefull to know it it's a CyberGFX/Picasso96 mode
but the rest of the time you shouldn`t really care.

I can only imagine you`re trying to protect your software from
screen promotion utilities? I`ve had problems from those myself
but size/depth/native checks are enough to cover most issues.

Cheers,

Paul

