@NODE "Mail_917" "Re: Weird machine hangups"
 for scott@online.u-net.com; Wed, 14 Apr 1999 12:50:08 +0100
From: "David McMinn" <D.Mcminn@eee.rgu.ac.uk>
Organization: The Robert Gordon University, E&EE
Date: Wed, 14 Apr 1999 12:47:31 +0100
encoding: Quoted-printable
Subject: Re: Weird machine hangups

>    I've attached the source code (entire) to my mod player (atm) as yet =
it
> doesnt really have any outstanding features, it just displays a gui with=
 a
> few buttons, and you just click on load etc. etc.
> 
> I've also attached the default shapes for it. copy this file to
> workbench:t/ or just change the src code.
> 
> Please could you test it to see if it hangs your machine before the gui
> appears. I don't know if its an enforcer hit, cos I ain't got an 030MMU.=
 

 DON'T do a vwait inside a SetInt 5, thats always a bad thing. Interrupts 
should not take longer than the time between successive interrupts of the =
same 
type occuring. In this case the setint 5 sets up some code to occur every 
frame, so your code should not take longer than a frame, or it will always=
 stay 
in the interrupt routine. Using VWait causes a delay until the next frame,=
 so 
you go straight back into the interrupt routine. Thus it appears that the 
computer has hung.

 Just from looking at your source, you might also need to change the way y=
ou 
set up the setint 5. You may need to wait for a module to be loaded and th=
en 
define your setint, and when a module is stoppped you would need to do Clr=
Int 5 
(to stop the module from trying to be played).

P.s. did you get that slider source I sent you?


