Well,.... It hangs my miggy, ... But before I go on,  I would just like to
know if ANYBODY knows how to use the bastard debugger?... Thats what it`s
there for ;)... And the #Stop# command. ... Did you try that?.. 
But no worriz... Just wondering....

Anyway, yeah to start with, the line...

s=ReadFile(1,setpath$)

crashes my mig,.. I dont know if it`s cos you are using PROGDIR, but I
wouldn`t advise that anyway,.. the easiest way to do stuff like that is:

DefaultDir$="Blitz2:Modplayer/" ;just an example

then,.. 

If ReadFile(1,DefaultDir$+"Settings")=True
etc,..
etc,..

And then when you make the final EXE, you just change:

DefaultDir$="Blitz2:Modplayer/"
DefaultDir$=""

And it works,.. I`ve had tonnes of problems with using PROGDIR: within
my code, but that doesn`t seem to be the main problem here....

If you stick #Stop# at the top of your code, and then compile it,...
Keep clicking the Step button until you reach the area it crashes,..
then you know which command is locking your amiga, reboot and 
step back to before the command that crashed, and do an Eval on the
variables to see what exactly you are passing to the command...

This is always the best way to debug things like this m8...

I havent fixed your code m8, cos there seems to be quite a lot of bugs in
there and you didn`t send the settings file.. I will say that the #Window#
command locked my miggy tho, i think you must be passing incorrect
dimensions to it...

[=> cheers.   
[=> Cya!
Regards
