> He says: "I wish computer games where more realistic."
> You say: "Yeah, like going to work, comming home, buying groceries."

I didnt say that but someone else. But as an article in the April issue
of Edge said too, a game is fun cause it does NOT match reality. Even
gran turismo is fun cause of the balance between reality and unreality.
Flightsims which go to absurd extremes to be realistic are only loved
by a few weirdo freaks who dont have a life.

If you would play a totally realistic rally game, you wouldnt be able
to win ever. You`d only be able to win if you`de be one of the lucky
few with enough talent to win in real life rally.  

This is just an example but think about it.

> I say: "Well obviously some people lead more interesting lives than you."

Some yes, I do :-) 

> My point is that a game doesn't have to be boring to be realistic, but offcourse since it would require alot of work, the other way is easier.

But mostly will be, believe it or not. The most unrealistic games were
and are the most fun. A head eating dots in a maze, shooting endles
flogs of monsters etc. etc.

Realistic games(meaning really realistic) will never appeal to the
masses.

Regards


