Date: Sat, 03 Apr 1999 20:07:38 +0000
Organization: personal
Subject: What? Mildred? CNKI file format? naaa :)

--BOUNDARY.1747972808.1

Orrite Geezaz!

Ive just finnished a new chunky file format called CNKI for use with Mildred
It stores either a chunky shape, or a chunky anim shape :)

Theres a proggy called BrushConvertor that converts IFF brush/animbrush files
to cnki files and an include file call CNKI.bb2 which contains a LoadCNK{}
command which is very similar to the loadshape() command, and it also
contains a CnkFrames{} command which returns the number of frames in a CNKI
file :))

Ohh by the way it also uses compression, 4.5k to 800 bytes hehehe
the only drawback to the compression when converting animbrushes is that u
can't use the last colour when creating your animbrushes ie colour 255,
it's to do with how the bytes work :)

Any way thought u guyz would like it so ive attached it :)

ceyaz

Chris.
