On 29-Apr-99, Rob Hutchinson wrote:

C=it`s just automatically redrawn, if you resize an MUI window, there is
C=ALWAYS the backdrop image in the back, even before the program would have
C=had chance the redraw the image. How is this possible? Another example is

The backdrop is drawn before the gadgets et all. So it looks like its `always
there`. So when a window is drawn, mui firsts draws the bare window with
backdrop and then the gadgets.

C=a crashed or frozen MUI program, if you can manage to crash one that has 
C=a sizable window open with a backdrop picture in it, even though it`s 
C=crashed you can resize it and the backdrop redraws... Catch my drift?
C=Or am I just imagining things? :))

That is because mui takes care of redrawing the backdrop, not the program.

That doesnt mean mui is cool, is still sucks big time :-)

