it`s just automatically redrawn, if you resize an MUI window, there is
ALWAYS the backdrop image in the back, even before the program would have
had chance the redraw the image. How is this possible? Another example is
a crashed or frozen MUI program, if you can manage to crash one that has 
a sizable window open with a backdrop picture in it, even though it`s 
crashed you can resize it and the backdrop redraws... Catch my drift?
Or am I just imagining things? :))

Cya!
