@NODE "Mail_935" "Re: Window backdrops"
 for scott@online.u-net.com; Fri, 30 Apr 1999 00:01:23 +0000
Date: Thu, 29 Apr 1999 19:39:55 -0300 (ADT)
Sender: ah210@chebucto.ns.ca
From:	John Mason <ah210@chebucto.ns.ca>
Subject: Re: Window backdrops

On Thu, 29 Apr 1999, amorel wrote:

> The backdrop is drawn before the gadgets et all. So it looks like its `always
> there`. So when a window is drawn, mui firsts draws the bare window with
> backdrop and then the gadgets.

Actually (and this is going to sound picky) I think the OS takes care of
the pattern ; that's why when you crash a MUI program or resize a window
while it's doing something else, usually just the background is redrawn,
not the (MUI) gadgets.  For the same reason, you can still resize a "dead"
MUI program, and the zoom gadget still had an effect while all of the MUI
gadgets no longer work.  I don't know any of this for sure though;  it
just seems as though that's how it's all working. :)

--

