@NODE "Mail_937" "Windows + Pens"
 for scott@online.u-net.com; Tue, 27 Apr 1999 10:21:04 +0100
X-Originating-IP: [194.18.83.122]
From: "Peter Thor" <peterthor@hotmail.com>
Subject: Windows + Pens
Date: Tue, 27 Apr 1999 11:19:17 CEST

Hello folks!

How am I able to alter the palette a window uses when displaying a 
bitmap or a chunkybitmap?

Should I approach ObtainBestPenA() and LoadRGB32/4() in some way? 
(either one of LoadRGB32() or LoadRGB4())
As to my knowledge, LoadRGB32/4() alters the viewport of the 
specified screen to open the window on.

So how would I do it?

Kind regards, Thor.

