@NODE "Mail_938" "Re: Windows + Pens"
 for scott@online.u-net.com; Tue, 27 Apr 1999 14:29:25 +0100
From: "Paul" <paulwest@stationone.demon.co.uk>
Organization: private
Date: 27 Apr 99 14:11:47 +0000
Subject: Re: Windows + Pens
Encoding: 7bit

> Hello folks!
> 
> How am I able to alter the palette a window uses when displaying a 
> bitmap or a chunkybitmap?
> 
> Should I approach ObtainBestPenA() and LoadRGB32/4() in some way? 
> (either one of LoadRGB32() or LoadRGB4())
> As to my knowledge, LoadRGB32/4() alters the viewport of the 
> specified screen to open the window on.

You've only got one palette for the whole screen, so if you wanted it
to use different colours you'd have to either change the whole palette
or remap the image before you give it to the window.

-- 
Paul.

