@NODE "Mail_940" "Windows and their size dadgets"
 for scott@online.u-net.com; Mon, 26 Apr 1999 19:57:27 +0100
From: Gareth Griffiths <gaz@jokerd.freeserve.co.uk>
Date: Mon, 26 Apr 1999 19:56:53 +0100
Organization: Joker Developments
Subject: Windows and their size dadgets

Hi,
   Is there an OS call to change the size of a window without using the
gadget?

I regularly boot with no startup to save mem on net stuff, but can't be
arsed to change the AmigaDOS window so that the screen titlebar is visible.
Can u change this in blitz and then quit the program so that the changes
are still there?

cheers    
Cya!
