@NODE "Mail_947" "Re: Windows with the OS!"
 for scott@online.u-net.com; Sun, 18 Apr 1999 17:37:05 +0100
From: "David McMinn" <D.Mcminn@eee.rgu.ac.uk>
Organization: The Robert Gordon University, E&EE
Date: Sun, 18 Apr 1999 17:35:16 +0100
encoding: Quoted-printable
Subject: Re: Windows with the OS!

>     Can any of you smart blokes (birds?).. Help me with the attached cod=
e?
> And please tell me why it guru`s my miggy.. I know it`s summat to do wit=
h
> the screen, I`m pretty sure of it.. And I think the WScreen pointer is
> wrong?..
> 
> Can anyone help? EEek!

 You need to use a .NewWindow, not a .Window, to define the stuff. And usi=
ng 
ActiveScreen could end up in disaster if the screen is not public, and if =
it 
is, then you need to set the screen type to #PUBLICSCREEN.

CloseWindow_ should be passed the *OurWin pointer, not &NewWin

FreeJack's code will also be useful when you come to getting messages and =
the 
like, coz you can't then use WaitEvent and the rest.


