@NODE "Mail_948" "Re: Windows with the OS!"
 for scott@online.u-net.com; Sun, 18 Apr 1999 17:54:21 +0100
From: "Dave" <dave@nbsamiga.demon.co.uk>
Subject: Re: Windows with the OS!
Date: Sun, 18 Apr 1999 17:53:44 +0100
	boundary="----=_NextPart_000_003C_01BE89C4.68869B80"

------=_NextPart_000_003C_01BE89C4.68869B80
	charset="iso-8859-1"
Encoding: 7bit

>    Can any of you smart blokes (birds?).. Help me with the attached code?
>And please tell me why it guru`s my miggy.. I know it`s summat to do with
>the screen, I`m pretty sure of it.. And I think the WScreen pointer is
>wrong?..

Hmm...didn`t check your source...but here was my attempt at os windows in
blitz. I tried to copy how blitz creates windows...so you can use the normal
blitz commands with the windows. You can`t use the WaitEvent, or Event
commands, or access the Gadget value, but I have supplied my own version of
these commands. As far as I can tell, the only things that won`t work are
cycle gadgets and radio buttons, as they were not in bb2.0, which it was
this include was made for. But it does open a os screen using screen_ (I
think it works...haven`t used it lately)...(Make sure you use my open screen
with my close screen, and do not forget to call init and remove at the start
and end of your programs!)...

You have to remember that this was done a VERY very long time ago, before I
had an A1200, and before I started using amigalibs.res, and stopped putting
nil.l=syscall_() all over the place. (ie, it could be made much
better...lots of peeks and pokes everywhere)

Hope that helps,

Dave


