@NODE "Mail_950" "Re: Windows with the OS!"
 for scott@online.u-net.com; Sun, 18 Apr 1999 18:11:38 +0100
From: "Dave" <dave@nbsamiga.demon.co.uk>
Subject: Re: Windows with the OS!
Date: Sun, 18 Apr 1999 18:10:26 +0100
	charset="iso-8859-1"
Encoding: 7bit

P.s. I mean`t to say Opens an Os Window ;)...and it has replacement for all
the blitz intuition values...like eventclass etc...anything that is returned
by event, or waitevent has a global replacement in my include. Other normal
commands, like attaching a gt list, or gadgets or drawing into the window,
or using font`s should work too :)...If I`ve supplied a command, then use my
version instead of the blitz version..if I haven`t then don`t! Oh, And it
attaches it to the currently used blitz screen...

Dave


