encoding: Quoted-printable
Subject: Re: Windows with the OS!

Hi Dave,

> it rawcode) anyone well unlike blitz mine works..woohoo!!)....I open my
> own msgport, and handle the events by hand, instead of trying to patch t=
he

Really? Don't you just let INtuition open the message poirt for you, or di=
d you 
do a thing that shared message ports, so that you could open as many windo=
ws as 
you want?

If you did that, I wouldn't mind getting my hands on that.

> Ummm...basically it allocates a block of mem (maximum windows*sizeof
> .window) at the start, which is the list of blitz windows. That`s why
> object lists maximums are fixed at compile time, and why you can only ha=
ve

Does it do that for final executables as well?

> And that`s exactly what It does :).....but you also need a hook in the
> window to a msg port...and you`d have to either make your own..like I di=
d
> (ie, non hacky way) or patch blitz`s msgport (which you`d have to find
> first). That`s how blitz event and waitevent work. Other than that my
> windows work just like normal for the rest of the commands.

 Thats the easy bit, I think Blitz windows have their own message port i.e=
. not 
IDCMP shared, so you can just use the Wait_ type commands, using the UserP=
ort 
field from the blitz window, within the intuition window structure thats 
pointed to by the blitz window ;)))

or in normal language

*w.Window=3DPeek.l(Addr Window(0))
wsigmask.l=3D1 LSL *w\UserPort\mp_SigBit

etc

At least I think that's what I've used. Whats *w\WindowPort for?


