@NODE "Mail_954" "WOA Disk Mag"
 for scott@online.u-net.com; Sun, 18 Apr 1999 14:35:39 +0100
From: "AMI-Gerbil" <ami-gerbil@ami-gerbil.freeserve.co.uk>
Subject: WOA Disk Mag
Date: Sun, 18 Apr 1999 14:35:42 +0100
	charset="iso-8859-1"
Encoding: 7bit

Hey All, when I was at the Blitz meeting last night i mentioned the WOA disk
mag and i was suprised to find out that most of you (if not all) had never
even heard of it let alone read it. So i decided to advertise it in here
just incase anyone is interested in getting a copy.

In the the WOA DM there are loads of reviews of the latest software and
hardware, also PD reviews, game reviews and articles about computing in
general. You can pick up you free copy at www.trogsoft.freeserve.co.uk (If
you cant think of a name on the enterence screen just click enter site) and
then select the WOA link downl the left side of the page. The webmaster of
this site told me yesterday that the site MAY be down soon, but im not
sure - if you are having trouble getting a copy i could send it to you
personaly or if there are enough ppl who want it and no-one objects i could
post it on here (one issue at a time - they are only about 350Kb each) It is
now in issue 3 and soon there will be a special edition to celebrate the
Amigas birthday which will be a HUGE issue with articles and interviews with
famous Amiga pplz :)

You can get issues 1 and 2 from my site at www.ami-gerbil.freeserve.co.uk
and on the main page, about 3/4 the way down there will be a small section
on the WOA disk mag, click on the one you want to download.

Any more problems contact me.

Enjoy.

-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-
  Sam Brookes - ICQ# 28871289
 AMI-Gerbil Software (AMI-Gerbil)
 stuff@ami-gerbil.freeserve.co.uk
 www.ami-gerbil.freeserve.co.uk
